// ============================================================================
// Volume Exhaustion Strategy [VES v2.1.0]
// Mean-reversion on volume exhaustion with Wave/ROC/Z-Score detection
// Optimized for Renko charts; Heiken-Ashi supported via HA chart type
// ============================================================================
// v2.1.1 CHANGES:
//   - NEW confluence: Spread Efficiency Qualifier (Q). On the current bar:
//     volume above its SMA AND candle spread below its SMA → exhaustion candle.
//     High volume that fails to move price is the classic signature of absorption.
//     Fires on the signal bar itself (not wave-level — complements R which is
//     wave-level). Scored as +1 confluence (Q) on every qualifying bar.
//     req_Q toggle (default OFF) makes it a hard gate when enabled.
//     Separate SMA length inputs for volume and spread (both default 20).
//   - conf_max bumped 8 → 9.
//   - Dashboard: Row 11 gains Q row (E/R shifts to 12, Confluence to 13, etc.),
//     debug gate row gains Q: status.
// ============================================================================
// v2.1.0 CHANGES:
//   - NEW confluence: Effort vs Result (R). Compares the counter-wave's
//     volume-per-point ratio (effort/result) against the dominant wave's
//     equivalent ratio. A counter-wave that burned disproportionately more
//     volume per unit of price movement confirms exhaustion and strengthens
//     the mean-reversion premise.
//     • Long: prev bear wave E/R ≥ prev bull wave E/R × er_mult
//     • Short: prev bull wave E/R ≥ prev bear wave E/R × er_mult
//     Price displacement source is user-selectable:
//       - Body |open-close|: cleaner on Heiken-Ashi (default)
//       - Wick high-low: full range, more conservative
//     req_R defaults ON — treated as a core confluence from day one.
//     NOTE: current implementation is absolute comparison (counter vs dominant).
//     TODO: upgrade to comparative mode (counter E/R vs its own rolling
//     historical average) in a future version for adaptive thresholding.
//   - conf_max bumped 7 → 8.
//   - Dashboard: confluence detail strings gain "R" letter; debug gate row
//     gains "R:" status cell; Row 11 reflects new conf_max.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.9 CHANGES:
//   - NEW: Signal Router — hidden meta-signals that bundle all longs and all
//     shorts into single alert conditions. Useful for webhook routing where
//     you don't care which confluence grade triggered — just "go long" or
//     "go short". Does not appear on chart. Access via alert conditions:
//       • "🟢 ROUTER: ANY LONG" — fires on any vol_bottom signal
//       • "🔴 ROUTER: ANY SHORT" — fires on any vol_peak signal
//     Alert message includes JSON payload with entry details for ATS/QuantLynk.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.8 CHANGES:
//   - FIX: Debug Mode now truly bypasses ALL gates including session.
//     Previously, debug mode still enforced session_gate — signals wouldn't
//     fire outside trading hours even with "ALL GATES BYPASSED" showing.
//     Now debug mode = flip_to_bull/bear only, no other gates checked.
//   - Dashboard debug row text updated to clarify behavior.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.7 CHANGES:
//   - NEW: Wave Compare debug labels. When debug mode is ON, visual labels show
//     raw Wave Compare triggers (exhaustion/climax) BEFORE gates filter them.
//     Labels display wave volumes (prev vs prev2) and trigger type (EXH/CLX).
//     Helps diagnose why Wave Compare fires or doesn't fire.
//   - NEW Wave Compare inputs in grp_vol:
//     • wave_use_exhaustion (ON) — toggle exhaustion detection (declining volume)
//     • wave_use_climax (ON) — toggle climax detection (blowoff/spike volume)
//     • wave_climax_mult (1.2) — minimum multiplier for climax vs prior wave
//     • wave_min_volume (0) — minimum cumulative wave volume to qualify
//   - NEW Debug input: debug_show_wave_labels (ON) — toggle Wave Compare labels
//     independently from full debug mode.
//   - Wave Compare logic updated to respect new toggles. Allows tuning which
//     pattern types (exhaustion vs climax) fire signals.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.6 CHANGES:
//   - BB demoted from hard gate to confluence only. bb_gate_long/short removed
//     from final signal formula. bb_ok_long_recent/short_recent still computed
//     and still contribute +1 to confluence score (conf_bb). req_B and
//     debug_require_bb inputs removed — no longer meaningful as gates.
//   - FIX: flip_to_bull/flip_to_bear added directly to final signal formula.
//     Previously flip was only enforced inside vol_bottom_raw (V path). With
//     V:OFF, signals fired on every bar meeting other conditions — not just
//     flip bars. Now flip is always required regardless of V setting.
//   - Dashboard gates row: BB removed from gate display; added to confluence
//     detail string instead.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.5 CHANGES:
//   - FIX: Hard stop loss was missing entirely. strategy.exit() calls had no
//     loss= parameter — only be_stop (requires favorable movement to activate)
//     and trail (same). If price went straight against entry, there was no stop.
//     Added sl_pts input (default 40pt) and sl_ticks computed from it.
//     All four strategy.exit() calls now include loss=sl_ticks.
//     Dashboard TP/TRAIL row updated to show SL value alongside TP and Trail.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.4 CHANGES:
//   - FIX: BB gate lookback upgraded from fixed 2-bar to per-wave boolean.
//     The prior wave is tracked for whether it EVER touched the BB edge during
//     its entire duration. On Renko, the flip bar is already 1 brick away from
//     the wave extreme; the old 2-bar window routinely missed valid band touches.
//     bb_ok_long_recent / bb_ok_short_recent now use per-wave state vars.
//   - FIX: Wave Compare warmup — when prev2_bear/bull_wave is 0 (first wave seen
//     in that direction), the signal was permanently blocked. Now the first wave
//     passes if prev_wave > 0, treating first observation as "exhausted by default".
//     Prevents dead-zone after gaps, rollovers, or one-sided morning sessions.
//   - FIX: Chop gate bootstrap — prior default of chop_min_avg for warmup period
//     meant first 4 waves had ZERO chop protection (5.0 < 5.0 = false). Default
//     now 0.0 until N waves measured, blocking entries until history is established.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.3 CHANGES:
//   - ADR fix: daily_high/daily_low now use [1] offset + lookahead_on to prevent
//     repainting from intraday daily bar updates.
//   - Added trail_activation_bricks input (grp_tp): Renko-native trail activation.
//     Trail starts tracking only after price moves N bricks in favor. Replaces
//     hardcoded trail_points=1 in strategy.exit() calls.
//   - HMA input tooltip clarified: documents dual roles — Hpx confluence (price
//     vs HMA position) AND HMA Gate (HMA vs EMA 21 cross).
//   - NEW grp_req "🎯 Confluence Requirements" group: req_V/req_B/req_S (default ON)
//     and req_H/req_E/req_W (default OFF). Makes each confluence factor optionally
//     required for a signal to fire, independent of debug toggles.
//   - Gate chain updated: req_* inputs incorporated into vol/bb/session gates;
//     new hpx_gate, ema_stack_gate, xwave_gate added to final signal logic.
//   - Trail activation plumbing: brick_safe/trail_act_pts/trail_act_ticks computed
//     and used in strategy.exit() trail_points parameter.
//   - Dashboard row 8 label: "Trend Gate" → "HMA Gate".
//   - Confluence detail strings: "H" → "Hpx" for clarity.
//   - Debug row 18: added Hpx/E/W gate status columns.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.2 CHANGES:
//   - Extracted VER constant — single source of truth for version string.
//   - Preset overrides: YM/NQ TP/trail now explicit (were relying on input defaults).
//   - Decomposed exhaust_val_text nested ternary into named intermediates.
//   - Fixed BB timeframe dashboard label (hardcoded "m" broke D/W/M).
//   - Deduplicated entry blocks: merged flatten-reverse + flat-enter branches.
//   - Extracted tooltip confluence strings to reduce label line length.
//   - Removed dead is_custom variable (CUSTOM works as preset fallthrough).
//   - Variable reference audit: all vars confirmed defined before use.
// ============================================================================
// v2.0.0 CHANGES:
//   - EMA stack: 9/15/34/233 → 21/34/50 (OHLC4). Slower, more deliberate trend read.
//   - Removed old Soft Trend Filter (EMA stack + 233 macro gate).
//   - HMA 20 source changed from close → OHLC4. Cross of HMA 20 through EMA 21
//     now serves as trend-warning gate (blocks signals when momentum shifts).
//   - NEW confluence: Cross-Wave Volume Ratio. Compares counter-wave volume to
//     dominant-wave volume when 21/34/50 is stacked. ≤50% = weak pop/dip, +1 confluence.
//   - BB Squeeze: replaced static 2×TP threshold with adaptive ratio — current
//     width must be ≥60% of its own 50-bar moving average.
//   - NEW gate: Wave Length Chop Detector. Average of last 5 wave lengths must
//     be ≥5 bricks. Prevents trading in flip-heavy chop environments.
//   - Confluence count: 6 → 7 (added cross-wave ratio W).
//   - Dashboard updated for new gates/confluences.
//   - All new thresholds exposed as inputs with conservative/aggressive tooltips.
// ============================================================================
//@version=6
VER = "2.1.1"
strategy("Volume Exhaustion Strategy [VES v" + VER + "]",
     overlay          = true,
     pyramiding       = 2,
     default_qty_type = strategy.fixed,
     default_qty_value= 1,
     initial_capital  = 25000,
     commission_type  = strategy.commission.cash_per_contract,
     commission_value = 2.25,
     slippage         = 3,
     calc_on_every_tick = true,
     max_labels_count = 500,
     max_bars_back    = 5000)

// ============================================================================
// INSTRUMENT PRESETS
// ============================================================================
grp_preset = "⚡ Instrument Preset"
preset = input.string("🔷 YM (Dow)", "Instrument",
     options=["🔷 YM (Dow)", "📈 NQ (NASDAQ)", "📊 ES (S&P)", "🛢️ CL (Crude)", "🟤 HG (Copper)", "⚙️ CUSTOM"],
     group=grp_preset,
     tooltip="Single dropdown to auto-configure all instrument-specific settings.\nSelect CUSTOM to use manual inputs for everything.\n\nPreset values (TP / Trail / Session / BE Bricks):\n🔷 YM/MYM: 40pt / 40pt / 0930-1145,1330-1600 / 3\n📈 NQ/MNQ: 40pt / 40pt / 0930-1145,1330-1600 / 3\n📊 ES/MES: 8pt / 8pt / 0930-1145,1330-1600 / 3\n🛢️ CL/MCL: 0.20 / 0.20 / 0900-1430 / 3\n🟤 HG: 0.0050 / 0.0050 / 0930-1145,1330-1600 / 3")

is_ym = preset == "🔷 YM (Dow)"
is_nq = preset == "📈 NQ (NASDAQ)"
is_es = preset == "📊 ES (S&P)"
is_cl = preset == "🛢️ CL (Crude)"
is_hg = preset == "🟤 HG (Copper)"

// ============================================================================
// CORE CONFIGURATION
// ============================================================================
grp_tp = "💰 TP & Trail"
tp_pts_in    = input.float(40.0, "Take Profit (points)", group=grp_tp, tooltip="Distance in price points from entry to TP. Each position exits independently when its TP is hit.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 40.0)")
sl_pts_in    = input.float(40.0, "Stop Loss (points)", group=grp_tp, minval=1.0, step=5.0, tooltip="Hard stop loss distance in price points from entry. This is the maximum loss per contract.\nFires immediately if price moves against entry by this amount — no favorable movement required.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 40.0)")
trail_mode   = input.string("Fixed", "Trail Mode", options=["Fixed", "ATR", "Wider of Both"], group=grp_tp,
     tooltip="Fixed: Uses the fixed Trail points value below.\nATR: Trail distance = ATR × multiplier. Adapts to current volatility.\nWider of Both: Uses whichever is larger — fixed or ATR. Gives a floor in calm markets, room in volatile ones.\n(Default: Fixed)")
trail_pts_in = input.float(40.0, "Trail Fixed (points)", group=grp_tp, tooltip="Fixed trail distance in points from the best price reached.\nUsed when Trail Mode is 'Fixed' or 'Wider of Both'.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 40.0)")
atr_trail_len = input.int(14, "ATR Length", group=grp_tp, minval=1, maxval=50, tooltip="Lookback period for ATR calculation. Used when Trail Mode is 'ATR' or 'Wider of Both'.\n(Default: 14)")
atr_trail_mult = input.float(1.5, "ATR Multiplier", group=grp_tp, minval=0.5, maxval=5.0, step=0.25, tooltip="Trail distance = ATR × this value. 1.0 = tight, 1.5 = standard, 2.0 = wide.\nUsed when Trail Mode is 'ATR' or 'Wider of Both'.\n(Default: 1.5)")
be_enable    = input.bool(true, "Enable Breakeven Stop", group=grp_tp, tooltip="Once price moves N Renko bricks in favor, the stop is moved to entry + offset ticks. Protects capital on trades that initially work then reverse.\n(Default: true)")
be_boxes_in  = input.int(3, "Bricks to Trigger BE", group=grp_tp, minval=1, maxval=20, tooltip="Number of Renko bricks price must move in your favor before the breakeven stop activates.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 3)")
be_ticks_in  = input.int(3, "BE Offset (ticks profit)", group=grp_tp, minval=0, maxval=20, tooltip="Once BE triggers, stop is placed at entry + this many ticks. 0 = true breakeven.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 3)")
trail_activation_bricks = input.int(1, "Trail Activation (bricks)", group=grp_tp, minval=1, maxval=5,
     tooltip="Number of Renko bricks price must move in your favor before the trailing stop begins tracking. Renko-native: 1 brick = one full brick_size move.\n1 = trail activates immediately on the next brick (standard). 2–3 = gives the trade more room before the trail engages, reducing premature exits on initial volatility.\nOn non-Renko charts, falls back to 8 × syminfo.mintick per 'brick'.\n(Default: 1)")
daily_dd_limit_in = input.float(3000.0, "Daily DD Limit ($)", group=grp_tp, minval=0, step=100,
     tooltip="Maximum daily drawdown in dollars. Flattens all positions and blocks entries for rest of day. Set to 0 to disable.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 3000)")
daily_pt_limit = input.float(0.0, "Daily Profit Target ($)", group=grp_tp, minval=0, step=100,
     tooltip="Daily profit target in dollars. Flattens and locks in the day when target hit. Set to 0 to disable.\n(Default: 0 = disabled)")

grp_adr = "📏 ADR Exhaustion Filter"
enable_adr_filter = input.bool(true, "Enable ADR Exhaustion Filter", group=grp_adr,
     tooltip="Suppresses new entries when today's range has consumed most of the average daily range. The day's move is likely done — don't enter late.\n(Default: true)")
adr_length = input.int(10, "ADR Lookback (days)", group=grp_adr, minval=1, maxval=50,
     tooltip="Number of trading days to average for the daily range baseline. 10 ≈ 2 weeks.\n(Default: 10)")
adr_exhaust_pct = input.float(80.0, "Exhaustion Threshold (%)", group=grp_adr, minval=50.0, maxval=100.0, step=5.0,
     tooltip="If today's high-low range exceeds this % of ADR, new signals are suppressed.\n80% = conservative (stops early). 95% = permissive (trades deeper into the day's range).\n(Default: 80)")
adr_tighten_trail = input.bool(true, "Tighten Trail When ADR > 70%", group=grp_adr,
     tooltip="When the day's range exceeds 70% of ADR, the trailing stop tightens by 30%. Locks in profits as the day's move exhausts.\n(Default: true)")
adr_tighten_pct = input.float(70.0, "Tighten Threshold (%)", group=grp_adr, minval=40.0, maxval=90.0, step=5.0,
     tooltip="Trail tightens when ADR usage exceeds this %. Lower = tighten earlier, higher = more room.\n(Default: 70)")

// --- Preset Overrides ---
// CUSTOM uses manual inputs. All other presets override specific values.
tp_pts        = is_cl ? 0.20 : is_hg ? 0.0050 : is_es ? 8.0 : is_ym or is_nq ? 40.0 : tp_pts_in
sl_pts        = is_cl ? 0.20 : is_hg ? 0.0050 : is_es ? 8.0 : is_ym or is_nq ? 40.0 : sl_pts_in
trail_fixed   = is_cl ? 0.20 : is_hg ? 0.0050 : is_es ? 8.0 : is_ym or is_nq ? 40.0 : trail_pts_in
be_boxes      = be_boxes_in
be_ticks      = be_ticks_in
daily_dd_limit = is_cl ? 2000.0 : daily_dd_limit_in
daily_dd_enabled = daily_dd_limit > 0
daily_pt_enabled = daily_pt_limit > 0

grp_vol = "📊 Volume Exhaustion Detection"
min_wave_len = input.int(3, "Min Wave Length (bricks)", group=grp_vol, minval=1, maxval=20,
     tooltip="Minimum number of consecutive same-direction bricks before a flip counts as a valid signal. Prevents whipsaw entries on 1-2 brick chop.\nConservative: 5 (only larger swings). Aggressive: 2 (most flips qualify).\n(Default: 3)")
vol_method = input.string("Wave Compare", "Detection Method", 
     options=["Wave Compare", "Volume ROC", "Z-Score", "OFF (flip + BB only)"], group=grp_vol,
     tooltip="Wave Compare: Compares cumulative volume of the ending wave vs prior same-direction wave. Exhaustion = declining wave volume while price extends. Best for Renko.\n\nVolume ROC: Detects volume acceleration/deceleration. Better for time-based/Heiken Ashi charts.\n\nZ-Score: Per-brick volume spike detection. Works poorly on Renko. Better on time-based charts.\n\nOFF: No volume gate — fires on every Renko flip that meets other conditions.\n(Default: Wave Compare)")
vol_lookback = input.int(20, "Volume Lookback (bars)", group=grp_vol, minval=5, maxval=200,
     tooltip="Rolling window for volume mean/std dev calculations.\n(Default: 20)")
wave_decline_pct = input.float(0.0, "Wave Volume Decline % (0=any decline)", group=grp_vol, minval=0.0, maxval=50.0, step=5.0,
     tooltip="For Wave Compare: minimum % decline in wave volume vs prior same-direction wave. 0 = any decline counts. 20 = wave must be 20%+ weaker.\nConservative: 20 (only clear exhaustion). Aggressive: 0 (any decline counts).\n(Default: 0)")
vol_roc_len = input.int(5, "ROC Smoothing (bars)", group=grp_vol, minval=2, maxval=20,
     tooltip="For Volume ROC: SMA smoothing on volume rate-of-change. Lower = more responsive.\n(Default: 5)")
z_threshold = input.float(0.3, "Z-Score Threshold", group=grp_vol, minval=0.1, maxval=4.0, step=0.1,
     tooltip="For Z-Score method only. 0.3 = permissive, 1.5 = selective.\n(Default: 0.3)")

// --- Wave Compare Fine-Tuning (v2.0.7) ---
wave_use_exhaustion = input.bool(true, "Wave: Enable Exhaustion Detection", group=grp_vol,
     tooltip="Exhaustion = ending wave has LESS volume than prior same-direction wave. Indicates sellers/buyers are tiring out.\nTurn OFF to ignore declining-volume patterns.\n(Default: ON)")
wave_use_climax = input.bool(true, "Wave: Enable Climax Detection", group=grp_vol,
     tooltip="Climax = ending wave has MORE volume than prior same-direction wave (blowoff/spike). Can indicate capitulation or exhaustion via excess.\nTurn OFF to ignore high-volume spike patterns.\n(Default: ON)")
wave_climax_mult = input.float(1.2, "Wave: Climax Multiplier", group=grp_vol, minval=1.0, maxval=3.0, step=0.1,
     tooltip="For climax detection: ending wave volume must be ≥ this × prior same-direction wave. 1.0 = any increase counts as climax. 1.5 = must be 50% higher. 2.0 = must be double.\nConservative: 1.5+ (only clear blowoffs). Aggressive: 1.0–1.2 (most increases qualify).\n(Default: 1.2)")
wave_min_volume = input.float(0.0, "Wave: Min Wave Volume (0=off)", group=grp_vol, minval=0.0, maxval=100000.0, step=100.0,
     tooltip="Minimum cumulative volume a wave must have to qualify for exhaustion/climax detection. Filters out low-volume noise waves.\n0 = no filter (all waves qualify). For YM/NQ, try 500–2000 depending on session.\n(Default: 0)")

grp_ema = "📈 Moving Averages (OHLC4)"
ema_fast_len  = input.int(21,  "EMA Fast (21)",  group=grp_ema, tooltip="Fast EMA on OHLC4 source. Part of the 21/34/50 trend stack. HMA 20 crossing this EMA triggers the trend-warning gate.\nConservative: 21 (standard). Aggressive: 18 (faster response).\n(Default: 21)")
ema_mid_len   = input.int(34,  "EMA Mid (34)",   group=grp_ema, tooltip="Mid EMA on OHLC4 source. Middle of the 21/34/50 alignment stack.\n(Default: 34)")
ema_slow_len  = input.int(50,  "EMA Slow (50)",  group=grp_ema, tooltip="Slow EMA on OHLC4 source. Anchor of the trend stack. Replaces the old 233 macro — the 50 provides sufficient trend context on Renko without lagging excessively.\nConservative: 50 (standard). Aggressive: 44 (faster unstack detection).\n(Default: 50)")

grp_bb = "📉 Bollinger Bands (MTF)"
bb_length_in = input.int(10, "BB Length", group=grp_bb, tooltip="Lookback period for the BB basis (SMA of close). Matches TradingView standard BB.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 10)")
bb_mult_in   = input.float(1.2, "BB Std Dev Multiplier", group=grp_bb, step=0.1, tooltip="Standard deviation multiplier for band width. 1.2 = tighter than standard 2.0 — catches mean-reversion entries closer to midline.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 1.2)")
bb_tf_in     = input.timeframe("3", "BB Calculation Timeframe", group=grp_bb, tooltip="Timeframe for BB calculation. Computed via request.security() and projected onto your Renko chart.\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n(Default: 3 minutes)")
bb_color_up  = input.color(#2962FF, "Upper Band", group=grp_bb, inline="bbc1", tooltip="(Default: #2962FF blue)")
bb_color_lo  = input.color(#2962FF, "Lower Band", group=grp_bb, inline="bbc1", tooltip="(Default: #2962FF blue)")
bb_color_mid = input.color(color.gray, "Midline", group=grp_bb, inline="bbc2", tooltip="(Default: gray)")
bb_squeeze_filter = input.bool(true, "Suppress Signals in BB Squeeze", group=grp_bb,
     tooltip="When enabled, blocks all signals when BB width is too narrow relative to its own recent average. Adaptive — auto-calibrates across sessions and instruments.\n(Default: true)")
bb_squeeze_ratio = input.float(0.60, "Squeeze Ratio (% of avg width)", group=grp_bb, minval=0.20, maxval=0.90, step=0.05,
     tooltip="Current BB width must be ≥ this ratio × the average BB width to allow signals. Below this = squeeze (chop zone).\nConservative: 0.70 (blocks more — stricter squeeze definition). Aggressive: 0.45 (allows trading in tighter ranges).\n(Default: 0.60)")
bb_squeeze_avg_len = input.int(50, "Squeeze Avg Lookback (bars)", group=grp_bb, minval=20, maxval=200, step=10,
     tooltip="Rolling window for BB width moving average used in squeeze detection. Longer = smoother baseline, adapts more slowly between sessions.\nConservative: 75 (very stable baseline). Aggressive: 30 (adapts faster to new conditions).\n(Default: 50)")

// BB preset overrides
bb_length = bb_length_in
bb_mult   = is_cl ? 1.4 : bb_mult_in
bb_tf     = is_cl ? "5" : bb_tf_in

grp_hma = "〰️ HMA (Chart TF)"
hma_length = input.int(20, "HMA Length", group=grp_hma, tooltip="Hull Moving Average length on OHLC4 source. Serves two roles:\n\n1. Hpx Confluence: Price position relative to HMA. Close below HMA = +1 long confluence (bearish structure). Close above HMA = +1 short confluence (bullish structure). This reflects the mean-reversion premise — entering against the HMA position.\n\n2. HMA Gate: HMA 20 crossing through EMA 21. HMA above EMA 21 = bullish momentum → shorts blocked. HMA below EMA 21 = bearish momentum → longs blocked. Gate can be disabled in Trend Filter group.\n\nConservative: 24 (fewer false crosses). Aggressive: 16 (faster momentum detection).\n(Default: 20)")

grp_trend = "🛡️ Trend Filter (HMA × EMA 21)"
use_trend_gate = input.bool(true, "Enable Trend Warning Gate", group=grp_trend,
     tooltip="When HMA 20 crosses through EMA 21, momentum is shifting. This gate blocks new signals in the direction that's losing momentum.\n\nHMA below EMA 21 → blocks longs (bearish momentum).\nHMA above EMA 21 → blocks shorts (bullish momentum).\n\nDisable to allow signals regardless of HMA/EMA alignment.\n(Default: true)")

grp_chop = "🔀 Chop Detector"
use_chop_filter = input.bool(true, "Enable Chop Detector", group=grp_chop,
     tooltip="Blocks all signals when recent waves are too short — the market is flipping back and forth with no follow-through. Measures the average length of the last N waves and requires it to be ≥ the minimum threshold.\n(Default: true)")
chop_wave_count = input.int(5, "Waves to Average", group=grp_chop, minval=3, maxval=10,
     tooltip="Number of recent completed waves to average for chop detection. More waves = more stable read but slower to adapt.\nConservative: 7 (needs more history). Aggressive: 3 (reacts faster).\n(Default: 5)")
chop_min_avg = input.float(5.0, "Min Avg Wave Length (bricks)", group=grp_chop, minval=2.0, maxval=15.0, step=0.5,
     tooltip="If the average wave length is below this, the market is choppy — all signals blocked. Once avg rises above this, the algo wakes up.\nConservative: 6 (stricter — needs bigger waves). Aggressive: 4 (allows shorter waves).\n(Default: 5.0)")

grp_xwave = "⚖️ Cross-Wave Volume Ratio"
xwave_threshold = input.float(0.50, "Max Counter-Wave Ratio", group=grp_xwave, minval=0.20, maxval=0.90, step=0.05,
     tooltip="When EMAs are stacked, this compares the counter-trend wave's volume to the dominant wave's volume. If the counter-wave is ≤ this ratio, the pop/dip was weak — adds +1 confluence confirming the dominant side still controls.\n\nExample at 0.50: In a bear stack, if the bullish pop had ≤50% of the prior bearish push's volume, the pop was hollow → confirms short bias.\n\nThis is a CONFLUENCE (adds to score), not a gate (does not block signals).\nConservative: 0.40 (only extremely weak counter-waves count). Aggressive: 0.65 (more lenient).\n(Default: 0.50)")

grp_er = "📐 Effort vs Result (E/R)"
er_range_source = input.string("Body (|open-close|)", "Price Displacement Source", options=["Body (|open-close|)", "Wick (high-low)"], group=grp_er,
     tooltip="How to measure the 'Result' (price displacement) of each wave.\n\nBody |open-close|: Cumulative body size per wave. Cleaner on Heiken-Ashi since wicks can be noise — recommended default for HA charts.\n\nWick high-low: Full bar range per wave. More conservative — captures all price movement including wicks.\n\n(Default: Body)")
er_mult = input.float(1.0, "E/R Ratio Multiplier", group=grp_er, minval=0.5, maxval=3.0, step=0.1,
     tooltip="The counter-wave's effort/result ratio must be ≥ this multiple of the dominant wave's ratio to qualify.\n\n1.0 = any higher ratio counts (counter burned more vol/pt than dominant).\n1.2 = counter must be 20% more inefficient than dominant (stricter).\n1.5 = counter must be 50% more inefficient (very selective).\n\nConservative: 1.3. Aggressive: 1.0.\n(Default: 1.0)")

grp_seq = "🔬 Spread Efficiency Qualifier (Q)"
seq_vol_len = input.int(20, "Volume SMA Length", group=grp_seq, minval=5, maxval=200,
     tooltip="Rolling SMA length for per-bar volume. The current bar's volume must be ABOVE this SMA to qualify.\n\nHigh volume on the signal bar is the 'effort' side of the equation — the market is working hard.\n\nConservative: 30 (needs sustained elevated volume). Aggressive: 10 (reacts faster to volume spikes).\n(Default: 20)")
seq_spread_len = input.int(20, "Spread SMA Length", group=grp_seq, minval=5, maxval=200,
     tooltip="Rolling SMA length for per-bar candle spread (high - low). The current bar's spread must be BELOW this SMA to qualify.\n\nNarrow spread despite high volume means price is not moving — the bar absorbed volume without making progress. This is the exhaustion signature.\n\nConservative: 30 (stricter baseline for 'narrow'). Aggressive: 10 (faster-adapting spread baseline).\n(Default: 20)")

grp_session = "⏰ Session Filter"
use_session = input.bool(true, "Enable Session Filter", group=grp_session, tooltip="When enabled, signals only fire during configured trading windows.\n(Default: true)")
session_str_in = input.string("0930-1145,1330-1600:23456", "Session Config", group=grp_session,
     tooltip="Format: TIME1,TIME2:DAYS (ET timezone)\nDays: 1=Sun 2=Mon 3=Tue 4=Wed 5=Thu 6=Fri 7=Sat\nOverridden by instrument preset unless CUSTOM is selected.\n\nPreset defaults:\nYM/NQ/ES/HG: 0930-1145,1330-1600:23456\nCL: 0900-1430:23456\n\nCommon additions:\nPre-market: 0830-0930\nLondon: 0200-0500\nAsia: 1800-2100\nExample with pre-market: 0830-0930,0930-1145,1330-1600:23456\n(Default: 0930-1145,1330-1600:23456)")
flatten_outside = input.bool(false, "Flatten Positions Outside Session", group=grp_session,
     tooltip="If enabled, all open positions are closed when the session window ends. If disabled, positions ride until TP/Trail/Opposite signal.\n(Default: false)")

// Session preset override
session_str = is_cl ? "0900-1430:23456" : session_str_in

grp_ats = "ATS COMPATIBILITY"
ats_flatten_enabled = input.bool(false, "⚠ READ TOOLTIP → ATS SAFETY FLATTEN", group=grp_ats,
     tooltip="Fires a flatten webhook to ATS whenever the strategy transitions to fully flat.\nCatches any position desync between the strategy and your broker.\n\nRequires a SECOND TradingView alert on this strategy:\n  Condition: This strategy → 'Any alert() function call'\n  Webhook URL: Your ATS webhook endpoint\n  Message: (leave default — alert() provides the payload)\n\nHarmless no-op if broker is already flat.\n(Default: false)")
ats_user_id  = input.string("", "ATS User ID", group=grp_ats,
     tooltip="Your ATS user identifier (format: xx_1234567890).\n(Default: empty)")
ats_spam_key = input.string("", "ATS Spam Key", group=grp_ats,
     tooltip="Your security passphrase from ATS. Field name in payload is 'spam-key' (hyphen).\n(Default: empty)")
ats_comment  = input.string("safety_flatten", "ATS Comment", group=grp_ats,
     tooltip="Free-form tag logged to the ATS trade record. Useful for identifying safety flatten events in your trade log.\n(Default: safety_flatten)")

grp_ql = "QUANTLYNK COMPATIBILITY"
ql_enabled  = input.bool(false, "Enable QuantLynk Alerts", group=grp_ql,
     tooltip="When enabled, all strategy calls include QuantLynk-formatted alert_message payloads.\nYou must also set your TradingView alert message to: {{strategy.order.alert_message}}\n(Default: false)")
ql_user_id  = input.string("", "QuantLynk User ID", group=grp_ql,
     tooltip="Your qv_user_id from QuantLynk. Find it in the webhook generator on the QuantLynk dashboard.\n(Default: empty)")
ql_alert_id = input.string("", "QuantLynk Alert ID", group=grp_ql,
     tooltip="Your alert_id from QuantLynk. Each alert target has a unique ID.\n(Default: empty)")

grp_vis = "🎨 Visuals"
color_candles   = input.bool(true, "Color Candles by Direction", group=grp_vis, tooltip="Colors Renko bricks by direction: bullish = blue, bearish = pink.\n(Default: true)")
show_labels     = input.bool(true, "Show VOL PEAK / VOL BOTTOM Labels", group=grp_vis, tooltip="Displays VEB/VEP arrow labels with exhaustion method and confluence count at signal bars.\n(Default: true)")
show_wick_dots  = input.bool(true, "Show Yellow Dots on EMA Wick Touches", group=grp_vis, tooltip="Visual-only yellow dots when a wick touches the selected EMA but price closes on the other side (bounce).\n(Default: true)")
wick_dot_ema    = input.string("EMA 34", "Wick Touch EMA", options=["EMA 21", "EMA 34", "EMA 50"], group=grp_vis, tooltip="Which EMA to detect wick touches on.\n(Default: EMA 34)")
bull_candle_col = input.color(#00BFFF, "Bullish Candle", group=grp_vis, inline="cc1", tooltip="(Default: #00BFFF cyan)")
bear_candle_col = input.color(#FF4081, "Bearish Candle", group=grp_vis, inline="cc1", tooltip="(Default: #FF4081 pink)")
ema21_color     = input.color(#FFFFFF, "EMA 21",  group=grp_vis, inline="ec1", tooltip="(Default: #FFFFFF white)")
ema34_color     = input.color(#FFD700, "EMA 34",  group=grp_vis, inline="ec1", tooltip="(Default: #FFD700 gold)")
ema50_color     = input.color(#00BFFF, "EMA 50",  group=grp_vis, inline="ec2", tooltip="(Default: #00BFFF cyan)")
hma_color       = input.color(#00FF00, "HMA 20",  group=grp_vis, inline="ec2", tooltip="(Default: #00FF00 lime green)")

grp_dash = "📋 Dashboard"
show_dash = input.bool(true, "Show Dashboard", group=grp_dash, tooltip="Shows the performance and status dashboard on the chart.\n(Default: true)")
dash_pos  = input.string("Top Right", "Position", options=["Top Right", "Bottom Right", "Top Left", "Bottom Left"], group=grp_dash, tooltip="Corner of the chart for the dashboard table.\n(Default: Top Right)")

// ============================================================================
// CHART TYPE DETECTION
// ============================================================================
is_renko    = chart.is_renko
chart_label = is_renko ? "RENKO" : chart.is_range ? "RANGE" : chart.is_heikinashi ? "HA" : "STD"
brick_size  = is_renko ? (high - low) : 0.0

// ============================================================================
// SESSION PARSING
// ============================================================================
config_parts  = str.split(session_str, ":")
times_str     = array.get(config_parts, 0)
days_str      = array.size(config_parts) > 1 ? array.get(config_parts, 1) : "23456"
time_windows  = str.split(times_str, ",")
num_windows   = array.size(time_windows)
day_suffix    = ":" + days_str

in_w1 = num_windows >= 1 ? not na(time(timeframe.period, str.trim(array.get(time_windows, 0)) + day_suffix, "America/New_York")) : false
in_w2 = num_windows >= 2 ? not na(time(timeframe.period, str.trim(array.get(time_windows, 1)) + day_suffix, "America/New_York")) : false
in_w3 = num_windows >= 3 ? not na(time(timeframe.period, str.trim(array.get(time_windows, 2)) + day_suffix, "America/New_York")) : false
in_w4 = num_windows >= 4 ? not na(time(timeframe.period, str.trim(array.get(time_windows, 3)) + day_suffix, "America/New_York")) : false

in_session_raw = in_w1 or in_w2 or in_w3 or in_w4
in_session     = not use_session or in_session_raw
session_just_closed = use_session and not in_session_raw and in_session_raw[1]

// ============================================================================
// MOVING AVERAGES (OHLC4 source — 21/34/50 stack)
// ============================================================================
ema_src  = ohlc4
ema_21   = ta.ema(ema_src, ema_fast_len)
ema_34   = ta.ema(ema_src, ema_mid_len)
ema_50   = ta.ema(ema_src, ema_slow_len)

// EMA trend stacking — 21/34/50
ema_stacked_bull = ema_21 > ema_34 and ema_34 > ema_50
ema_stacked_bear = ema_21 < ema_34 and ema_34 < ema_50

// ============================================================================
// HMA 20 (OHLC4 source — matches EMAs)
// ============================================================================
hma_val  = ta.hma(ohlc4, hma_length)
hma_bull = close > hma_val
hma_bear = close < hma_val
hma_rising  = hma_val > hma_val[1]
hma_falling = hma_val < hma_val[1]

// HMA × EMA 21 cross — trend warning gate
// HMA above EMA 21 = bullish momentum. HMA below EMA 21 = bearish momentum.
hma_above_ema21 = hma_val > ema_21
hma_below_ema21 = hma_val < ema_21

// ============================================================================
// BOLLINGER BANDS (MTF via request.security)
// ============================================================================
// Matches TradingView standard BB: SMA basis, close source
cleanTicker = ticker.new(syminfo.prefix, syminfo.ticker)

bb_src_calc(len, mult) =>
    basis = ta.sma(close, len)
    dev   = mult * ta.stdev(close, len)
    [basis, basis + dev, basis - dev]

[bb_basis, bb_upper, bb_lower] = request.security(cleanTicker, bb_tf, bb_src_calc(bb_length, bb_mult), gaps=barmerge.gaps_off, lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_on)

// Price position relative to bands
price_at_lower_bb = close <= bb_lower
price_at_upper_bb = close >= bb_upper
price_below_mid   = close < bb_basis
price_above_mid   = close > bb_basis

// BB Bandwidth — adaptive squeeze detection (v2.0.0)
bb_width_pts = nz(bb_upper - bb_lower, 0.0)
bb_width_avg = ta.sma(bb_width_pts, bb_squeeze_avg_len)
bb_squeeze_threshold = nz(bb_width_avg, 0.0) * bb_squeeze_ratio
bb_is_squeezed = bb_squeeze_filter and bb_squeeze_threshold > 0 and bb_width_pts < bb_squeeze_threshold

// Squeeze release: was squeezed, now expanding back above threshold
bb_squeeze_release = bb_is_squeezed[1] and not bb_is_squeezed

// ============================================================================
// ATR TRAILING STOP CALCULATION
// ============================================================================
atr_val = ta.atr(atr_trail_len)
atr_trail_dist = atr_val * atr_trail_mult

// Resolve trail distance based on mode
trail_pts_resolved = trail_mode == "ATR" ? atr_trail_dist : trail_mode == "Wider of Both" ? math.max(trail_fixed, atr_trail_dist) : trail_fixed

// ============================================================================
// ADR EXHAUSTION FILTER
// ============================================================================
rth_is_open = not na(time(timeframe.period, "0930-1600:23456", "America/New_York"))
rth_just_opened = rth_is_open and not rth_is_open[1]

var float rth_high = na
var float rth_low = na

if rth_just_opened
    rth_high := high
    rth_low  := low
else if rth_is_open
    rth_high := math.max(nz(rth_high, high), high)
    rth_low  := math.min(nz(rth_low, low), low)

rth_range = nz(rth_high - rth_low, 0.0)

// ADR calculation using daily timeframe
// [1] offset + lookahead_on prevents repainting from intraday daily bar updates —
// we want yesterday's confirmed range, not the still-forming today range.
daily_high = request.security(cleanTicker, "D", high[1], lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_on)
daily_low  = request.security(cleanTicker, "D", low[1],  lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_on)
daily_range = nz(daily_high - daily_low, 0.0)
adr_val = nz(ta.sma(daily_range, adr_length), 0.0)
adr_pct_used = adr_val > 0 ? (rth_range / adr_val) * 100 : 0.0
adr_ok = not enable_adr_filter or adr_pct_used < adr_exhaust_pct

// ADR trail tightening — reduce trail by 30% when approaching exhaustion
adr_tightening = adr_tighten_trail and adr_pct_used >= adr_tighten_pct
trail_pts = adr_tightening ? trail_pts_resolved * 0.7 : trail_pts_resolved

// ============================================================================
// VOLUME EXHAUSTION DETECTION — 3 Methods + OFF
// ============================================================================

// --- Brick Direction ---
bull_brick    = close >= open
bear_brick    = close < open
raw_flip_bull = bull_brick and not bull_brick[1]
raw_flip_bear = bear_brick and not bear_brick[1]

// --- Wave Length Counter ---
var int wave_len = 0
wave_len := bull_brick == bull_brick[1] ? wave_len + 1 : 1

var int prev_wave_len = 0
if raw_flip_bull or raw_flip_bear
    prev_wave_len := nz(wave_len[1], 1)

flip_to_bull = raw_flip_bull and prev_wave_len >= min_wave_len
flip_to_bear = raw_flip_bear and prev_wave_len >= min_wave_len

// --- BB Per-Wave Tracker (v2.0.4) ---
// raw_flip_* is now defined — track whether each wave EVER touched the band.
// Placed here so raw_flip_bull/bear are available. price_at_lower/upper_bb
// are defined above in the BB section and are always available.
var bool cur_wave_lower_bb  = false
var bool cur_wave_upper_bb  = false
var bool prev_wave_lower_bb = false
var bool prev_wave_upper_bb = false

if raw_flip_bull or raw_flip_bear
    prev_wave_lower_bb := cur_wave_lower_bb
    prev_wave_upper_bb := cur_wave_upper_bb
    cur_wave_lower_bb  := price_at_lower_bb
    cur_wave_upper_bb  := price_at_upper_bb
else
    cur_wave_lower_bb  := cur_wave_lower_bb or price_at_lower_bb
    cur_wave_upper_bb  := cur_wave_upper_bb or price_at_upper_bb

// Gate passes if current flip bar is at the band OR if the prior wave touched it
bb_ok_long_recent  = price_at_lower_bb or prev_wave_lower_bb
bb_ok_short_recent = price_at_upper_bb or prev_wave_upper_bb
// Tracks the last N completed wave lengths. If average is below threshold, market is choppy.
var array<float> wave_len_history = array.new_float(0)

if raw_flip_bull or raw_flip_bear
    array.push(wave_len_history, float(nz(wave_len[1], 1)))
    if array.size(wave_len_history) > chop_wave_count
        array.shift(wave_len_history)

// Default to 0.0 (not chop_min_avg) during warmup so the gate BLOCKS until
// N waves are measured. Prior default of chop_min_avg meant 5.0 < 5.0 = false
// — first 4 waves had zero chop protection.
avg_wave_len = array.size(wave_len_history) >= chop_wave_count ? array.avg(wave_len_history) : 0.0
is_choppy = use_chop_filter and avg_wave_len < chop_min_avg

// --- Base Volume Data ---
has_vol   = not na(volume) and volume > 0
vol_safe  = has_vol ? volume : 0.0

// ============================================================================
// METHOD 1: Wave Volume Compare (Weis Wave style)
// ============================================================================
var float wave_cum_vol      = 0.0
var float prev_bull_wave    = 0.0
var float prev_bear_wave    = 0.0
var float prev2_bull_wave   = 0.0
var float prev2_bear_wave   = 0.0

// --- Wave Price Displacement Accumulators (v2.1.0 — Effort vs Result) ---
// Track cumulative price displacement per wave in parallel with volume.
// Body: |open - close| per bar — recommended for Heiken-Ashi (wick noise filtered).
// Wick: high - low per bar — full range, more conservative.
// On flip: snapshot completed wave's displacement to prev_bear/bull_disp vars.
var float wave_cum_body     = 0.0   // cumulative |open-close| of current wave
var float wave_cum_wick     = 0.0   // cumulative (high-low) of current wave
var float prev_bull_body    = 0.0   // body displacement of last completed bull wave
var float prev_bear_body    = 0.0   // body displacement of last completed bear wave
var float prev_bull_wick    = 0.0   // wick range of last completed bull wave
var float prev_bear_wick    = 0.0   // wick range of last completed bear wave

if raw_flip_bull
    prev2_bear_wave := prev_bear_wave
    prev_bear_wave  := wave_cum_vol
    prev_bear_body  := wave_cum_body
    prev_bear_wick  := wave_cum_wick
    wave_cum_vol    := vol_safe
    wave_cum_body   := math.abs(open - close)
    wave_cum_wick   := high - low
else if raw_flip_bear
    prev2_bull_wave := prev_bull_wave
    prev_bull_wave  := wave_cum_vol
    prev_bull_body  := wave_cum_body
    prev_bull_wick  := wave_cum_wick
    wave_cum_vol    := vol_safe
    wave_cum_body   := math.abs(open - close)
    wave_cum_wick   := high - low
else
    wave_cum_vol  += vol_safe
    wave_cum_body += math.abs(open - close)
    wave_cum_wick += (high - low)

// Wave exhaustion: the ending wave had LESS volume than the prior same-direction wave.
// Warmup fix: when prev2 is still 0 (only 1 prior wave observed), allow the signal
// if prev_wave > 0 — we saw selling/buying pressure end and flip, which is sufficient.
// Prevents permanent block after gaps, rollovers, or one-sided morning sessions.
// v2.0.7: Added wave_min_volume filter and wave_use_exhaustion toggle.
wave_decline_thresh = 1.0 - (wave_decline_pct / 100.0)

// Min volume filter — wave must have enough volume to be meaningful
wave_bear_vol_ok = prev_bear_wave >= wave_min_volume
wave_bull_vol_ok = prev_bull_wave >= wave_min_volume

// Exhaustion detection (declining volume) — toggled by wave_use_exhaustion
wave_bear_exhausted_raw = (prev2_bear_wave == 0 and prev_bear_wave > 0) or
                          (prev2_bear_wave > 0 and prev_bear_wave < (prev2_bear_wave * wave_decline_thresh))
wave_bull_exhausted_raw = (prev2_bull_wave == 0 and prev_bull_wave > 0) or
                          (prev2_bull_wave > 0 and prev_bull_wave < (prev2_bull_wave * wave_decline_thresh))
wave_bear_exhausted = wave_use_exhaustion and wave_bear_vol_ok and wave_bear_exhausted_raw
wave_bull_exhausted = wave_use_exhaustion and wave_bull_vol_ok and wave_bull_exhausted_raw

// Climax detection (blowoff volume) — v2.0.7: uses wave_climax_mult and wave_use_climax toggle
// prev_wave must be ≥ climax_mult × prev2_wave to qualify as a climax
wave_bear_climax_raw = prev2_bear_wave > 0 and prev_bear_wave >= (prev2_bear_wave * wave_climax_mult)
wave_bull_climax_raw = prev2_bull_wave > 0 and prev_bull_wave >= (prev2_bull_wave * wave_climax_mult)
wave_bear_climax = wave_use_climax and wave_bear_vol_ok and wave_bear_climax_raw
wave_bull_climax = wave_use_climax and wave_bull_vol_ok and wave_bull_climax_raw

wave_vol_bottom = flip_to_bull and has_vol and (wave_bear_exhausted or wave_bear_climax)
wave_vol_peak   = flip_to_bear and has_vol and (wave_bull_exhausted or wave_bull_climax)

// ============================================================================
// METHOD 2: Volume Rate of Change (ROC)
// ============================================================================
vol_sma_fast = ta.sma(vol_safe, vol_roc_len)
vol_sma_slow = ta.sma(vol_safe, vol_lookback)
vol_roc_val  = vol_sma_slow > 0 ? ((vol_sma_fast - vol_sma_slow) / vol_sma_slow) * 100 : 0.0

vol_decelerating = vol_roc_val < vol_roc_val[1]
vol_below_avg = vol_sma_fast <= vol_sma_slow

roc_vol_bottom = flip_to_bull and has_vol and (vol_decelerating or vol_below_avg)
roc_vol_peak   = flip_to_bear and has_vol and (vol_decelerating or vol_below_avg)

// ============================================================================
// METHOD 3: Z-Score
// ============================================================================
vol_sma_z = ta.sma(vol_safe, vol_lookback)
vol_std   = ta.stdev(vol_safe, vol_lookback)
vol_z     = vol_std > 0 ? (vol_safe - vol_sma_z) / vol_std : 0.0

zscore_vol_bottom = flip_to_bull and has_vol and vol_z >= z_threshold
zscore_vol_peak   = flip_to_bear and has_vol and vol_z >= z_threshold

// ============================================================================
// METHOD SELECTOR
// ============================================================================
use_wave = vol_method == "Wave Compare"
use_roc  = vol_method == "Volume ROC"
use_z    = vol_method == "Z-Score"

vol_bottom_raw = use_wave ? wave_vol_bottom : use_roc ? roc_vol_bottom : use_z ? zscore_vol_bottom : (flip_to_bull and has_vol)
vol_peak_raw   = use_wave ? wave_vol_peak   : use_roc ? roc_vol_peak   : use_z ? zscore_vol_peak   : (flip_to_bear and has_vol)

// Method label for dashboard
vol_method_label = use_wave ? "WAVE" : use_roc ? "ROC" : use_z ? "Z-SCR" : "OFF"

// ============================================================================
// CROSS-WAVE VOLUME RATIO (v2.0.0 — Confluence)
// ============================================================================
// When EMAs are stacked, compare the counter-trend wave's volume to the
// dominant wave's volume. If counter-wave ≤ threshold, the pop/dip was weak.
// This confirms the dominant side still controls. Added as +1 confluence.

// For longs in bull stack: bear dip volume vs bull push volume
// prev_bear_wave = the dip that just ended, prev_bull_wave = the prior bull push
xwave_long_ok  = ema_stacked_bull and prev_bull_wave > 0 and prev_bear_wave <= (prev_bull_wave * xwave_threshold)

// For shorts in bear stack: bull pop volume vs bear push volume
// prev_bull_wave = the pop that just ended, prev_bear_wave = the prior bear push
xwave_short_ok = ema_stacked_bear and prev_bear_wave > 0 and prev_bull_wave <= (prev_bear_wave * xwave_threshold)

// ============================================================================
// EFFORT VS RESULT (v2.1.0 — Confluence "R")
// ============================================================================
// Measures how much volume (effort) was required per unit of price movement
// (result) for each completed wave. A counter-wave with a higher effort/result
// ratio than the dominant wave is burning energy without moving price —
// classic exhaustion confirmation.
//
// Formula:
//   E/R ratio = cumulative_wave_volume / cumulative_wave_price_displacement
//
// Long signal (bear counter-wave ending): bear E/R ≥ bull E/R × er_mult
//   → The bear wave was inefficient relative to the bull wave — bears exhausted.
//
// Short signal (bull counter-wave ending): bull E/R ≥ bear E/R × er_mult
//   → The bull wave was inefficient relative to the bear wave — bulls exhausted.
//
// Price displacement source selected via er_range_source input:
//   "Body (|open-close|)": cumulative body size — cleaner on Heiken-Ashi (default)
//   "Wick (high-low)": cumulative full-range — more conservative, catches all movement
//
// NOTE: This is an absolute comparison (counter vs dominant wave).
// TODO: Upgrade to comparative mode in a future version — counter E/R vs its own
// rolling historical average — for adaptive thresholding across sessions/instruments.
// ============================================================================

use_body_disp = er_range_source == "Body (|open-close|)"

// Select displacement source per configuration
prev_bear_disp = use_body_disp ? prev_bear_body : prev_bear_wick
prev_bull_disp = use_body_disp ? prev_bull_body : prev_bull_wick

// Compute E/R ratios — guard against zero displacement to avoid division by zero
// A zero displacement wave (all doji-like bars) returns 0.0 — treated as no data
bear_er_ratio = prev_bear_disp > 0 ? prev_bear_wave / prev_bear_disp : 0.0
bull_er_ratio = prev_bull_disp > 0 ? prev_bull_wave / prev_bull_disp : 0.0

// Long: counter-wave was bear — bear E/R must exceed bull E/R × multiplier
er_long_ok  = bull_er_ratio > 0.0 and bear_er_ratio >= (bull_er_ratio * er_mult)

// Short: counter-wave was bull — bull E/R must exceed bear E/R × multiplier
er_short_ok = bear_er_ratio > 0.0 and bull_er_ratio >= (bear_er_ratio * er_mult)

// ============================================================================
// SPREAD EFFICIENCY QUALIFIER (v2.1.1 — Confluence "Q")
// ============================================================================
// Bar-level exhaustion check — complements R (which is wave-level).
// Condition: volume above its SMA AND candle spread below its SMA.
// High volume that fails to produce price movement = absorption.
// The market is working hard but going nowhere — classic exhaustion bar.
//
// Fires on the current bar (signal bar). Does not require wave history.
// Scored as +1 confluence (Q) on every qualifying bar.
// req_Q (default OFF) promotes it to a hard gate when enabled.
// ============================================================================
vol_sma_seq    = ta.sma(vol_safe, seq_vol_len)
spread_current = high - low
spread_sma_seq = ta.sma(spread_current, seq_spread_len)

seq_ok = has_vol and vol_safe > vol_sma_seq and spread_current < spread_sma_seq

// ============================================================================
// DEBUG CONTROLS
// ============================================================================
debug_mode = input.bool(false, "🔧 DEBUG: Bypass all gates (flip only)", group="🔧 Debug",
     tooltip="When ON, signals fire on every Renko direction flip regardless of all gates. Use to verify the engine works, then turn OFF.\n(Default: false)")
debug_require_vol = input.bool(true, "🔧 Require Volume Exhaustion", group="🔧 Debug",
     tooltip="Toggle volume exhaustion gate. Turn OFF to see if volume is blocking signals.\n(Default: true)")
debug_require_trend = input.bool(true, "🔧 Require Trend Gate (HMA×EMA21)", group="🔧 Debug",
     tooltip="Toggle HMA×EMA21 trend warning gate. Turn OFF to allow signals regardless of HMA position relative to EMA 21.\n(Default: true)")
debug_require_session = input.bool(true, "🔧 Require Session Filter", group="🔧 Debug",
     tooltip="Toggle session time filter. Turn OFF to allow signals outside trading hours.\n(Default: true)")
debug_require_chop = input.bool(true, "🔧 Require Chop Detector", group="🔧 Debug",
     tooltip="Toggle chop detector. Turn OFF to allow signals during choppy wave patterns.\n(Default: true)")
debug_show_wave_labels = input.bool(true, "🔧 Show Wave Compare Labels", group="🔧 Debug",
     tooltip="When ON (and Debug Mode is ON), displays visual labels showing raw Wave Compare triggers BEFORE gates filter them.\nShows exhaustion (EXH) and climax (CLX) detections with wave volumes.\nHelps diagnose why Wave Compare is or isn't firing.\n(Default: true)")

// ============================================================================
// CONFLUENCE REQUIREMENTS
// ============================================================================
// Independent of debug toggles — these make each confluence factor REQUIRED
// for a signal to fire. Default: V/B/S required (core gates), H/E/W optional.
// ============================================================================
grp_req = "🎯 Confluence Requirements"
req_V = input.bool(true,  "Require Volume Exhaustion (V)", group=grp_req,
     tooltip="When ON, a signal only fires if volume exhaustion is confirmed by the selected method (Wave/ROC/Z-Score/OFF).\nTurn OFF to allow signals without volume confirmation — useful for testing or if volume data is unavailable.\n(Default: ON)")
req_S = input.bool(true,  "Require Session Window (S)", group=grp_req,
     tooltip="When ON, signals only fire inside configured session windows.\nTurn OFF to allow signals at any time — useful for testing or running overnight sessions.\n(Default: ON)")
req_H = input.bool(false, "Require Hpx Confluence (H)", group=grp_req,
     tooltip="When ON, longs require close BELOW HMA (mean-reversion into bearish structure) and shorts require close ABOVE HMA.\nThis is the Hpx confluence factor — price position vs HMA, NOT the HMA Gate (HMA vs EMA 21).\nTurn ON for stricter mean-reversion entries. Keep OFF if you want signals regardless of price/HMA relationship.\n(Default: OFF)")
req_E = input.bool(false, "Require EMA Stack (E)", group=grp_req,
     tooltip="When ON, longs require 21>34>50 (bull stack) and shorts require 21<34<50 (bear stack).\nEnsures trades are in the direction of the trend stack. Reduces counter-trend signals but significantly reduces trade count in mixed/transitional markets.\n(Default: OFF)")
req_W = input.bool(false, "Require Cross-Wave Ratio (W)", group=grp_req,
     tooltip="When ON, signals require the counter-wave volume to be ≤ the configured ratio vs the dominant wave.\nEnsures only 'hollow' counter-waves qualify. Reduces trade count but increases confidence in dominant-side continuation.\nOnly active when EMAs are stacked (no stack = no cross-wave data).\n(Default: OFF)")
req_R = input.bool(true,  "Require Effort vs Result (R)", group=grp_req,
     tooltip="When ON, signals require the counter-wave's volume-per-point ratio (effort/result) to be ≥ the dominant wave's equivalent ratio × the multiplier.\n\nA counter-wave that burned disproportionately more volume per unit of price confirms exhaustion and the mean-reversion premise.\n\nTurn OFF to allow signals regardless of E/R relationship.\n(Default: ON — core confluence)")
req_Q = input.bool(false, "Require Spread Efficiency (Q)", group=grp_req,
     tooltip="When ON, signals require the current bar to be a spread efficiency candle: volume above its SMA AND spread (high-low) below its SMA.\n\nThis confirms absorption on the signal bar itself — the market is expending effort without producing price movement, the textbook exhaustion signature on Heiken-Ashi.\n\nKeep OFF to use Q as a bonus confluence score only. Turn ON for maximum precision at the cost of trade frequency.\n(Default: OFF)")

// --- BB: confluence only (v2.0.6) — still computed for +1 confluence score ---
// bb_ok_long/short retained for confluence counter; no longer used as a gate.
bb_ok_long  = bb_ok_long_recent and not bb_is_squeezed
bb_ok_short = bb_ok_short_recent and not bb_is_squeezed

// --- Build final gate chain with individual toggles + req_* requirements ---
// flip_to_bull/bear always required — ensures signals only fire on Renko direction
// flips regardless of whether V gate is ON or OFF.
vol_gate_long  = not req_V or not debug_require_vol or vol_bottom_raw
vol_gate_short = not req_V or not debug_require_vol or vol_peak_raw

// Session gate
session_gate_long  = not req_S or not debug_require_session or in_session
session_gate_short = not req_S or not debug_require_session or in_session

// Trend gate (v2.0.0): HMA × EMA 21 cross
// Longs blocked when HMA below EMA 21 (bearish momentum)
// Shorts blocked when HMA above EMA 21 (bullish momentum)
trend_gate_long  = not debug_require_trend or not use_trend_gate or hma_above_ema21
trend_gate_short = not debug_require_trend or not use_trend_gate or hma_below_ema21

// Hpx gate (v2.0.3): price position relative to HMA — mean-reversion premise
// Long: close below HMA (entering into bearish structure)
// Short: close above HMA (entering into bullish structure)
hpx_gate_long  = not req_H or hma_bear
hpx_gate_short = not req_H or hma_bull

// EMA stack gate (v2.0.3): requires full 21/34/50 alignment
ema_stack_gate_long  = not req_E or ema_stacked_bull
ema_stack_gate_short = not req_E or ema_stacked_bear

// Cross-wave ratio gate (v2.0.3): requires hollow counter-wave when stacked
xwave_gate_long  = not req_W or xwave_long_ok
xwave_gate_short = not req_W or xwave_short_ok

// Effort vs Result gate (v2.1.0): requires counter-wave E/R ≥ dominant E/R × multiplier
er_gate_long  = not req_R or er_long_ok
er_gate_short = not req_R or er_short_ok

// Spread Efficiency gate (v2.1.1): requires absorption candle on the signal bar
seq_gate = not req_Q or seq_ok

// Chop gate (v2.0.0)
chop_gate = not debug_require_chop or not is_choppy

// Shared session gate (backward compat — used in flatten/session checks)
session_gate = not debug_require_session or in_session

// --- Final Signals ---
// flip_to_bull/bear is always the base requirement (v2.0.6).
// bb_gate removed — BB is now confluence only.
// v2.0.8: Debug mode now truly bypasses ALL gates — flip only, no session check.
vol_bottom = debug_mode ? flip_to_bull : (flip_to_bull and vol_gate_long  and trend_gate_long  and hpx_gate_long  and ema_stack_gate_long  and xwave_gate_long  and er_gate_long  and seq_gate and session_gate_long  and adr_ok and chop_gate)
vol_peak   = debug_mode ? flip_to_bear : (flip_to_bear and vol_gate_short and trend_gate_short and hpx_gate_short and ema_stack_gate_short and xwave_gate_short and er_gate_short and seq_gate and session_gate_short and adr_ok and chop_gate)

// ============================================================================
// CONFLUENCE COUNTER (7 factors — v2.0.0)
// ============================================================================

// 1. Renko flip (always required, always 1 if signal fires)
conf_flip_long  = flip_to_bull ? 1 : 0
conf_flip_short = flip_to_bear ? 1 : 0

// 2. Volume exhaustion (method-dependent)
conf_vol_long  = vol_bottom_raw ? 1 : 0
conf_vol_short = vol_peak_raw   ? 1 : 0

// 3. BB outside bands (within 2 bars)
conf_bb_long  = bb_ok_long_recent  ? 1 : 0
conf_bb_short = bb_ok_short_recent ? 1 : 0

// 4. Session window active
conf_session = in_session_raw ? 1 : 0

// 5. HMA position (price below for long, above for short)
conf_hma_long  = hma_bear ? 1 : 0
conf_hma_short = hma_bull ? 1 : 0

// 6. EMA alignment (21/34/50 stacked)
conf_ema_long  = ema_stacked_bull ? 1 : 0
conf_ema_short = ema_stacked_bear ? 1 : 0

// 7. Cross-Wave Volume Ratio (v2.0.0)
conf_xwave_long  = xwave_long_ok  ? 1 : 0
conf_xwave_short = xwave_short_ok ? 1 : 0

// 8. Effort vs Result (v2.1.0)
conf_er_long  = er_long_ok  ? 1 : 0
conf_er_short = er_short_ok ? 1 : 0

// 9. Spread Efficiency Qualifier (v2.1.1)
conf_seq = seq_ok ? 1 : 0

// Total confluence count
conf_total_long  = conf_flip_long  + conf_vol_long  + conf_bb_long  + conf_session + conf_hma_long  + conf_ema_long  + conf_xwave_long  + conf_er_long  + conf_seq
conf_total_short = conf_flip_short + conf_vol_short + conf_bb_short + conf_session + conf_hma_short + conf_ema_short + conf_xwave_short + conf_er_short + conf_seq
conf_max = 9

// Exhaustion label text (method-specific value)
wave_decl_or_clmx_bear = wave_bear_exhausted ? "WvDecl" : wave_bear_climax ? "WvClmx" : ""
wave_decl_or_clmx_bull = wave_bull_exhausted ? "WvDecl" : wave_bull_climax ? "WvClmx" : ""
wave_label = flip_to_bull ? wave_decl_or_clmx_bear : flip_to_bear ? wave_decl_or_clmx_bull : ""
exhaust_val_text = use_wave ? wave_label : use_roc ? "ROC:" + str.tostring(vol_roc_val, "0.0") + "%" : use_z ? "Z:" + str.tostring(vol_z, "0.1") : ""
wave_len_text = str.tostring(prev_wave_len) + "b"

// ============================================================================
// POSITION MANAGEMENT
// ============================================================================
net_pos   = strategy.position_size
is_flat   = net_pos == 0
is_long   = net_pos > 0
is_short  = net_pos < 0
num_units = math.round(math.abs(net_pos))

// ============================================================================
// WEBHOOK PAYLOADS
// ============================================================================

// --- QuantLynk ---
ql_buy     = ql_enabled ? '{"qv_user_id": "' + ql_user_id + '", "alert_id": "' + ql_alert_id + '", "quantity": "1", "order_type": "market", "price": {{close}}, "action": "buy"}' : ''
ql_sell    = ql_enabled ? '{"qv_user_id": "' + ql_user_id + '", "alert_id": "' + ql_alert_id + '", "quantity": "1", "order_type": "market", "price": {{close}}, "action": "sell"}' : ''
ql_flatten = ql_enabled ? '{"qv_user_id": "' + ql_user_id + '", "alert_id": "' + ql_alert_id + '", "action": "flatten"}' : ''
ql_exit    = ql_enabled ? '{"qv_user_id": "' + ql_user_id + '", "alert_id": "' + ql_alert_id + '", "quantity": "1", "order_type": "market", "price": {{close}}, "action": "{{strategy.order.action}}"}' : ''

// --- ATS Safety Flatten ---
ats_flatten_payload = ats_flatten_enabled ? '{"contract": "{{ticker}}", "trade_type": "exit", "quantity": 1, "price": {{close}}, "spam-key": "' + ats_spam_key + '", "user_id": "' + ats_user_id + '", "strategy": 0, "comment": "' + ats_comment + '"}' : ''

// Convert points to ticks for strategy.exit()
tp_ticks    = math.round(tp_pts / syminfo.mintick)
sl_ticks    = math.round(sl_pts / syminfo.mintick)
trail_ticks = math.round(trail_pts / syminfo.mintick)

// Trail activation: Renko-native — N bricks must move in favor before trail begins
// brick_safe falls back to 8 ticks on non-Renko charts
brick_safe       = brick_size > 0 ? brick_size : syminfo.mintick * 8
trail_act_pts    = trail_activation_bricks * brick_safe
trail_act_ticks  = math.max(1, math.round(trail_act_pts / syminfo.mintick))

// --- Track entry prices for dashboard display ---
var float entry1_price = na
var float entry2_price = na
var int   pos_dir      = 0
var float highest_since = na
var float lowest_since  = na

// --- Breakeven Stop Tracking (per position) ---
var bool  be1_triggered = false
var bool  be2_triggered = false
be_offset_pts = be_ticks * syminfo.mintick
be_dist_pts   = is_renko ? be_boxes * brick_size : be_boxes * syminfo.mintick * 8

// Reset on flat + safety flatten
if is_flat and not is_flat[1]
    entry1_price := na
    entry2_price := na
    pos_dir      := 0
    highest_since := na
    lowest_since  := na
    be1_triggered := false
    be2_triggered := false
    if ats_flatten_enabled
        alert(ats_flatten_payload, alert.freq_once_per_bar)
    if ql_enabled
        alert(ql_flatten, alert.freq_once_per_bar)

// Track high/low water marks for trail display
if not is_flat
    highest_since := na(highest_since) ? high : math.max(highest_since, high)
    lowest_since  := na(lowest_since)  ? low  : math.min(lowest_since, low)

// --- Breakeven Trigger Detection ---
if be_enable and not na(entry1_price) and not be1_triggered
    if is_long  and high >= entry1_price + be_dist_pts
        be1_triggered := true
    if is_short and low  <= entry1_price - be_dist_pts
        be1_triggered := true

if be_enable and not na(entry2_price) and not be2_triggered
    if is_long  and high >= entry2_price + be_dist_pts
        be2_triggered := true
    if is_short and low  <= entry2_price - be_dist_pts
        be2_triggered := true

// BE stop price levels
be_stop_l1 = be1_triggered and is_long  ? entry1_price + be_offset_pts : na
be_stop_l2 = be2_triggered and is_long  ? entry2_price + be_offset_pts : na
be_stop_s1 = be1_triggered and is_short ? entry1_price - be_offset_pts : na
be_stop_s2 = be2_triggered and is_short ? entry2_price - be_offset_pts : na

// ============================================================================
// DAILY P&L TRACKING
// ============================================================================
is_new_day = ta.change(time("D")) != 0

var float equity_at_day_open = strategy.equity
var float daily_pnl          = 0.0
var bool  daily_dd_hit       = false
var bool  daily_pt_hit       = false
var int   daily_wins         = 0
var int   daily_losses       = 0
var int   daily_trades       = 0

if is_new_day
    equity_at_day_open  := strategy.equity
    daily_pnl           := 0.0
    daily_dd_hit        := false
    daily_pt_hit        := false
    daily_wins          := 0
    daily_losses        := 0
    daily_trades        := 0

daily_pnl := strategy.equity - equity_at_day_open

total_closed = strategy.closedtrades
var int prev_total_closed = 0
new_close = total_closed > prev_total_closed
if new_close
    new_count = total_closed - prev_total_closed
    daily_trades += new_count
    // Check each newly closed trade (handles multiple closes per bar)
    if total_closed > 0
        for i = 0 to new_count - 1
            trade_idx = total_closed - 1 - i
            if trade_idx >= 0
                trade_profit = strategy.closedtrades.profit(trade_idx)
                if trade_profit > 0
                    daily_wins += 1
                else if trade_profit < 0
                    daily_losses += 1
    prev_total_closed := total_closed

if daily_dd_enabled and daily_pnl <= -daily_dd_limit and not daily_dd_hit
    daily_dd_hit := true
    strategy.close_all(comment="DAILY DD LIMIT", alert_message=ql_flatten)

if daily_pt_enabled and daily_pnl >= daily_pt_limit and not daily_pt_hit
    daily_pt_hit := true
    strategy.close_all(comment="DAILY PT HIT", alert_message=ql_flatten)

daily_ok = not daily_dd_hit and not daily_pt_hit

// ============================================================================
// ENTRIES
// ============================================================================

// --- VOL BOTTOM → LONG ---
if vol_bottom and daily_ok
    conf_text_l = str.tostring(conf_total_long) + "/" + str.tostring(conf_max)
    if is_short
        strategy.close_all(comment="FLATTEN→L", alert_message=ql_flatten)
    if is_short or is_flat
        strategy.entry("L1", strategy.long, qty=1, comment="VEB D:1/2 " + conf_text_l, alert_message=ql_buy)
        entry1_price  := close
        entry2_price  := na
        pos_dir       := 1
        highest_since := high
        lowest_since  := low
        be1_triggered := false
        be2_triggered := false
    else if is_long and num_units < 2
        strategy.entry("L2", strategy.long, qty=1, comment="VEB D:2/2 " + conf_text_l, alert_message=ql_buy)
        entry2_price  := close
        be2_triggered := false

// --- VOL PEAK → SHORT ---
if vol_peak and daily_ok
    conf_text_s = str.tostring(conf_total_short) + "/" + str.tostring(conf_max)
    if is_long
        strategy.close_all(comment="FLATTEN→S", alert_message=ql_flatten)
    if is_long or is_flat
        strategy.entry("S1", strategy.short, qty=1, comment="VEP D:1/2 " + conf_text_s, alert_message=ql_sell)
        entry1_price  := close
        entry2_price  := na
        pos_dir       := -1
        highest_since := high
        lowest_since  := low
        be1_triggered := false
        be2_triggered := false
    else if is_short and num_units < 2
        strategy.entry("S2", strategy.short, qty=1, comment="VEP D:2/2 " + conf_text_s, alert_message=ql_sell)
        entry2_price  := close
        be2_triggered := false

// ============================================================================
// EXITS — TP + Trailing Stop + Breakeven per position
// ============================================================================
if is_long
    strategy.exit("XL1", from_entry="L1", profit=tp_ticks, loss=sl_ticks, trail_points=trail_act_ticks, trail_offset=trail_ticks,
         stop=be_stop_l1, comment_profit="TP +" + str.tostring(tp_pts, "#.##"), comment_loss=be1_triggered ? "BE+" + str.tostring(be_ticks) + "t" : "TRL", alert_message=ql_exit)
    strategy.exit("XL2", from_entry="L2", profit=tp_ticks, loss=sl_ticks, trail_points=trail_act_ticks, trail_offset=trail_ticks,
         stop=be_stop_l2, comment_profit="TP +" + str.tostring(tp_pts, "#.##"), comment_loss=be2_triggered ? "BE+" + str.tostring(be_ticks) + "t" : "TRL", alert_message=ql_exit)

if is_short
    strategy.exit("XS1", from_entry="S1", profit=tp_ticks, loss=sl_ticks, trail_points=trail_act_ticks, trail_offset=trail_ticks,
         stop=be_stop_s1, comment_profit="TP +" + str.tostring(tp_pts, "#.##"), comment_loss=be1_triggered ? "BE+" + str.tostring(be_ticks) + "t" : "TRL", alert_message=ql_exit)
    strategy.exit("XS2", from_entry="S2", profit=tp_ticks, loss=sl_ticks, trail_points=trail_act_ticks, trail_offset=trail_ticks,
         stop=be_stop_s2, comment_profit="TP +" + str.tostring(tp_pts, "#.##"), comment_loss=be2_triggered ? "BE+" + str.tostring(be_ticks) + "t" : "TRL", alert_message=ql_exit)

// --- Flatten outside session (optional) ---
if flatten_outside and session_just_closed and not is_flat
    strategy.close_all(comment="SESSION END", alert_message=ql_flatten)

// ============================================================================
// VISUAL ELEMENTS
// ============================================================================

// --- EMA Plots (21/34/50) ---
plot(ema_21,  "EMA 21",  color=color.new(ema21_color, 20),  linewidth=1)
plot(ema_34,  "EMA 34",  color=color.new(ema34_color, 20),  linewidth=1)
plot(ema_50,  "EMA 50",  color=color.new(ema50_color, 10),  linewidth=2)

// --- HMA 20 ---
plot(hma_val, "HMA 20", color=color.new(hma_color, 30), linewidth=2, style=plot.style_line)

// --- Bollinger Bands (MTF) ---
p_bb_upper = plot(bb_upper, "BB Upper", color=color.new(bb_color_up, 40), linewidth=1)
p_bb_lower = plot(bb_lower, "BB Lower", color=color.new(bb_color_lo, 40), linewidth=1)
plot(bb_basis, "BB Mid", color=color.new(bb_color_mid, 60), linewidth=1, style=plot.style_cross)
fill(p_bb_upper, p_bb_lower, color=color.new(bb_color_up, 92), title="BB Fill")

// --- Candle Coloring ---
candle_col = not color_candles ? na :
     bull_brick ? color.new(bull_candle_col, 0) :
     color.new(bear_candle_col, 0)
barcolor(candle_col)

// --- Tooltip confluence breakdown (pre-built to reduce label line length) ---
conf_str_long  = "Flip:✓ Vol:" + (conf_vol_long  > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " BB:" + (conf_bb_long  > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " Sess:" + (conf_session > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " Hpx:" + (conf_hma_long  > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " EMA:" + (conf_ema_long  > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " XWv:" + (conf_xwave_long  > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " R:" + (conf_er_long  > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " Q:" + (conf_seq > 0 ? "✓" : "✗")
conf_str_short = "Flip:✓ Vol:" + (conf_vol_short > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " BB:" + (conf_bb_short > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " Sess:" + (conf_session > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " Hpx:" + (conf_hma_short > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " EMA:" + (conf_ema_short > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " XWv:" + (conf_xwave_short > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " R:" + (conf_er_short > 0 ? "✓" : "✗") + " Q:" + (conf_seq > 0 ? "✓" : "✗")

// --- VOL PEAK / VOL BOTTOM Labels ---
if show_labels and vol_bottom
    units = is_short ? 1 : (is_flat ? 1 : math.min(num_units + 1, 2))
    lbl_text = "VEB " + exhaust_val_text + "\n" + wave_len_text + " " + str.tostring(conf_total_long) + "/" + str.tostring(conf_max)
    tip = "VOL BOTTOM — D:" + str.tostring(units) + "/2\nTP:" + str.tostring(close + tp_pts, "#.##") + " SL:" + str.tostring(close - sl_pts, "#.##") + " TRL-" + str.tostring(trail_pts, "#.##") + "\n" + conf_str_long
    label.new(bar_index, low, lbl_text,
         style=label.style_label_up, color=#00E676, textcolor=color.white,
         size=size.small, yloc=yloc.belowbar, tooltip=tip)

if show_labels and vol_peak
    units = is_long ? 1 : (is_flat ? 1 : math.min(num_units + 1, 2))
    lbl_text = "VEP " + exhaust_val_text + "\n" + wave_len_text + " " + str.tostring(conf_total_short) + "/" + str.tostring(conf_max)
    tip = "VOL PEAK — D:" + str.tostring(units) + "/2\nTP:" + str.tostring(close - tp_pts, "#.##") + " SL:" + str.tostring(close + sl_pts, "#.##") + " TRL-" + str.tostring(trail_pts, "#.##") + "\n" + conf_str_short
    label.new(bar_index, high, lbl_text,
         style=label.style_label_down, color=#FF6D00, textcolor=color.white,
         size=size.small, yloc=yloc.abovebar, tooltip=tip)

// --- Yellow Dots on EMA Wick Touches ---
wick_ema = wick_dot_ema == "EMA 21" ? ema_21 : wick_dot_ema == "EMA 50" ? ema_50 : ema_34

wick_touch_bull = low <= wick_ema and close > wick_ema
wick_touch_bear = high >= wick_ema and close < wick_ema

if show_wick_dots and wick_touch_bull and in_session
    label.new(bar_index, low, "•", style=label.style_none, textcolor=color.yellow, size=size.small, yloc=yloc.belowbar)
if show_wick_dots and wick_touch_bear and in_session
    label.new(bar_index, high, "•", style=label.style_none, textcolor=color.yellow, size=size.small, yloc=yloc.abovebar)

// ============================================================================
// WAVE COMPARE DEBUG LABELS (v2.0.7)
// ============================================================================
// Shows raw Wave Compare triggers BEFORE gates filter them.
// Only visible when debug_mode AND debug_show_wave_labels are both ON.
// Labels appear on flip bars showing:
//   - Trigger type: EXH (exhaustion) or CLX (climax) or NONE
//   - Wave volumes: prev vs prev2 for the relevant direction
//   - Pass/fail status for each detection type
// ============================================================================
if debug_mode and debug_show_wave_labels and use_wave
    // Build diagnostic info for bullish flip (checking bear wave exhaustion/climax)
    if raw_flip_bull
        // Determine what triggered (or didn't)
        bear_exh_status = not wave_use_exhaustion ? "OFF" : not wave_bear_vol_ok ? "MINVOL" : wave_bear_exhausted_raw ? "✓" : "✗"
        bear_clx_status = not wave_use_climax ? "OFF" : not wave_bear_vol_ok ? "MINVOL" : wave_bear_climax_raw ? "✓" : "✗"
        
        trigger_type = wave_bear_exhausted ? "EXH" : wave_bear_climax ? "CLX" : "NONE"
        trigger_col = wave_bear_exhausted or wave_bear_climax ? color.new(#00BCD4, 20) : color.new(#9E9E9E, 40)
        
        // Wave volume comparison
        wave_pct = prev2_bear_wave > 0 ? (prev_bear_wave / prev2_bear_wave) * 100 : 0.0
        wave_ratio_text = prev2_bear_wave > 0 ? str.tostring(wave_pct, "0") + "%" : "1st"
        
        // Flip qualification
        flip_status = flip_to_bull ? "✓" : "✗" + str.tostring(prev_wave_len) + "b"
        
        lbl_text = "🔍 WAVE\n" + trigger_type
        tip = "Wave Compare Debug (Bull Flip)\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "Flip OK: " + flip_status + " (min " + str.tostring(min_wave_len) + "b)\n" +
              "Has Vol: " + (has_vol ? "✓" : "✗") + "\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "BEAR WAVE (just ended):\n" +
              "  Vol: " + str.tostring(prev_bear_wave, "#,##0") + "\n" +
              "  Prev2: " + str.tostring(prev2_bear_wave, "#,##0") + "\n" +
              "  Ratio: " + wave_ratio_text + "\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "Exhaustion: " + bear_exh_status + " (decline ≥" + str.tostring(wave_decline_pct, "0") + "%)\n" +
              "Climax: " + bear_clx_status + " (mult ≥" + str.tostring(wave_climax_mult, "0.0") + "x)\n" +
              "Min Vol: " + str.tostring(wave_min_volume, "#,##0") + "\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "RESULT: " + (wave_vol_bottom ? "✓ VOL BOTTOM" : "✗ NO TRIGGER")
        
        label.new(bar_index, low, lbl_text,
             style=label.style_label_up, color=trigger_col, textcolor=color.white,
             size=size.tiny, yloc=yloc.belowbar, tooltip=tip)
    
    // Build diagnostic info for bearish flip (checking bull wave exhaustion/climax)
    if raw_flip_bear
        // Determine what triggered (or didn't)
        bull_exh_status = not wave_use_exhaustion ? "OFF" : not wave_bull_vol_ok ? "MINVOL" : wave_bull_exhausted_raw ? "✓" : "✗"
        bull_clx_status = not wave_use_climax ? "OFF" : not wave_bull_vol_ok ? "MINVOL" : wave_bull_climax_raw ? "✓" : "✗"
        
        trigger_type = wave_bull_exhausted ? "EXH" : wave_bull_climax ? "CLX" : "NONE"
        trigger_col = wave_bull_exhausted or wave_bull_climax ? color.new(#FF9800, 20) : color.new(#9E9E9E, 40)
        
        // Wave volume comparison
        wave_pct = prev2_bull_wave > 0 ? (prev_bull_wave / prev2_bull_wave) * 100 : 0.0
        wave_ratio_text = prev2_bull_wave > 0 ? str.tostring(wave_pct, "0") + "%" : "1st"
        
        // Flip qualification
        flip_status = flip_to_bear ? "✓" : "✗" + str.tostring(prev_wave_len) + "b"
        
        lbl_text = "🔍 WAVE\n" + trigger_type
        tip = "Wave Compare Debug (Bear Flip)\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "Flip OK: " + flip_status + " (min " + str.tostring(min_wave_len) + "b)\n" +
              "Has Vol: " + (has_vol ? "✓" : "✗") + "\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "BULL WAVE (just ended):\n" +
              "  Vol: " + str.tostring(prev_bull_wave, "#,##0") + "\n" +
              "  Prev2: " + str.tostring(prev2_bull_wave, "#,##0") + "\n" +
              "  Ratio: " + wave_ratio_text + "\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "Exhaustion: " + bull_exh_status + " (decline ≥" + str.tostring(wave_decline_pct, "0") + "%)\n" +
              "Climax: " + bull_clx_status + " (mult ≥" + str.tostring(wave_climax_mult, "0.0") + "x)\n" +
              "Min Vol: " + str.tostring(wave_min_volume, "#,##0") + "\n" +
              "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n" +
              "RESULT: " + (wave_vol_peak ? "✓ VOL PEAK" : "✗ NO TRIGGER")
        
        label.new(bar_index, high, lbl_text,
             style=label.style_label_down, color=trigger_col, textcolor=color.white,
             size=size.tiny, yloc=yloc.abovebar, tooltip=tip)

// --- Trail Level Display ---
trail_level_long  = is_long  and not na(highest_since) ? highest_since - trail_pts : na
trail_level_short = is_short and not na(lowest_since)  ? lowest_since  + trail_pts : na
plot(trail_level_long,  "Trail (Long)",  color=color.new(color.red, 50),   linewidth=1, style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(trail_level_short, "Trail (Short)", color=color.new(color.green, 50), linewidth=1, style=plot.style_linebr)

// --- TP Level Display ---
tp_level_long  = is_long  and not na(entry1_price) ? entry1_price + tp_pts : na
tp_level_short = is_short and not na(entry1_price) ? entry1_price - tp_pts : na
plot(tp_level_long,  "TP (Long)",  color=color.new(#00BFFF, 40), linewidth=1, style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(tp_level_short, "TP (Short)", color=color.new(#00BFFF, 40), linewidth=1, style=plot.style_linebr)

// --- Breakeven Level Display ---
be_level_long  = be_enable and be1_triggered and is_long  ? entry1_price + be_offset_pts : na
be_level_short = be_enable and be1_triggered and is_short ? entry1_price - be_offset_pts : na
plot(be_level_long,  "BE (Long)",  color=color.new(color.yellow, 30), linewidth=1, style=plot.style_linebr)
plot(be_level_short, "BE (Short)", color=color.new(color.yellow, 30), linewidth=1, style=plot.style_linebr)

// ============================================================================
// PERFORMANCE DASHBOARD (19 rows)
// ============================================================================
dash_position = switch dash_pos
    "Top Right"    => position.top_right
    "Bottom Right" => position.bottom_right
    "Top Left"     => position.top_left
    "Bottom Left"  => position.bottom_left
    => position.top_right

var table dash = table.new(dash_position, 3, 19, border_width=1,
     frame_color=color.new(color.white, 80), border_color=color.new(color.gray, 85))

if show_dash and barstate.islast
    // Colors
    bg_header = color.new(#1a1a2e, 0)
    bg_row    = color.new(#16213e, 0)
    txt       = color.white

    // Stats
    closed     = strategy.closedtrades
    wins       = strategy.wintrades
    losses     = strategy.losstrades
    win_rate   = closed > 0 ? (wins / closed) * 100 : 0.0
    net_pnl    = strategy.netprofit
    gross_win  = strategy.grossprofit
    gross_loss = math.abs(strategy.grossloss)
    pf         = gross_loss > 0 ? gross_win / gross_loss : 0.0
    expectancy = closed > 0 ? net_pnl / closed : 0.0
    avg_win    = wins > 0 ? gross_win / wins : 0.0
    avg_loss   = losses > 0 ? gross_loss / losses : 0.0
    max_dd     = math.abs(strategy.max_drawdown)

    // Position info
    pos_text = is_flat ? "FLAT" : is_long ? "LONG D:" + str.tostring(num_units) + "/2" : "SHORT D:" + str.tostring(num_units) + "/2"
    pos_col  = is_flat ? color.new(color.gray, 60) : is_long ? color.new(color.green, 50) : color.new(color.red, 50)

    // Signal state
    sig_text = vol_bottom ? "VEB" : vol_peak ? "VEP" : "scanning"
    sig_col  = vol_bottom ? color.new(#00E676, 50) : vol_peak ? color.new(#FF6D00, 50) : color.new(color.gray, 70)

    // Trail level
    trl_val  = is_long ? highest_since - trail_pts : is_short ? lowest_since + trail_pts : na
    trl_text = not na(trl_val) ? str.tostring(trl_val, "#.##") : "—"

    // Chart info
    renko_info = is_renko ? chart_label + " " + str.tostring(brick_size, "#.##") : chart_label

    // Preset label
    preset_lbl = is_ym ? "🔷 YM" : is_nq ? "📈 NQ" : is_es ? "📊 ES" : is_cl ? "🛢️ CL" : is_hg ? "🟤 HG" : "⚙️ CUSTOM"

    // Row 0: Header
    dbg_label = debug_mode ? " 🔧 DEBUG" : ""
    table.cell(dash, 0, 0, "VES v" + VER, bgcolor=bg_header, text_color=#00BFFF, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 0, preset_lbl + " | " + renko_info + dbg_label, bgcolor=debug_mode ? color.new(#FF6B00, 30) : bg_header, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 0, "", bgcolor=bg_header)

    // Row 1: TP/TRAIL
    trail_mode_lbl = trail_mode == "ATR" ? "ATR" : trail_mode == "Wider of Both" ? "MAX" : "FIX"
    trail_tight_lbl = adr_tightening ? " ⚡" : ""
    table.cell(dash, 0, 1, "TP/SL/TRAIL", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 1, str.tostring(tp_pts, "#.##") + "pt TP  " + str.tostring(sl_pts, "#.##") + "pt SL", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=#00BFFF, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 1, str.tostring(trail_pts, "#.##") + "pt " + trail_mode_lbl + trail_tight_lbl, bgcolor=adr_tightening ? color.new(color.orange, 50) : bg_row, text_color=#00BFFF, text_size=size.normal)

    // Row 2: Signal + Chop Status
    chop_text = is_choppy ? " ⛔CHOP" : ""
    table.cell(dash, 0, 2, "SIGNAL", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 2, sig_text + chop_text, bgcolor=is_choppy ? color.new(color.orange, 40) : sig_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 2, "Avg:" + str.tostring(avg_wave_len, "0.1") + "b", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=is_choppy ? color.orange : color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 3: Position
    table.cell(dash, 0, 3, "Position", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 3, pos_text, bgcolor=pos_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 3, "Trl:" + trl_text, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.orange, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 4: Session
    sess_text = use_session ? (in_session_raw ? "✓ ACTIVE" : "✗ OUTSIDE") : "OFF"
    sess_col  = not use_session ? color.new(color.gray, 80) : in_session_raw ? color.new(color.green, 60) : color.new(color.orange, 60)
    sess_window = in_w1 ? "W1" : in_w2 ? "W2" : in_w3 ? "W3" : in_w4 ? "W4" : "—"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 4, "Session", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 4, sess_text, bgcolor=sess_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 4, sess_window, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=in_session_raw ? color.green : color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 5: Daily P&L
    dpnl_col = daily_dd_hit ? color.new(#FF0000, 30) : daily_pt_hit ? color.new(#00FF00, 30) : daily_pnl >= 0 ? color.new(color.green, 50) : daily_pnl > -daily_dd_limit * 0.5 ? color.new(color.orange, 50) : color.new(color.red, 50)
    dpnl_text = "$" + str.tostring(daily_pnl, "#,##0")
    dpnl_status = daily_dd_hit ? " ⛔ DD LIMIT" : daily_pt_hit ? " 🎯 TARGET HIT" : ""
    dpnl_limits = (daily_dd_enabled ? "-$" + str.tostring(daily_dd_limit, "#,##0") : "") + (daily_dd_enabled and daily_pt_enabled ? " / " : "") + (daily_pt_enabled ? "+$" + str.tostring(daily_pt_limit, "#,##0") : "")
    dpnl_trades_text = str.tostring(daily_trades) + "t " + str.tostring(daily_wins) + "W/" + str.tostring(daily_losses) + "L"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 5, "Daily P&L", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 5, dpnl_text + dpnl_status, bgcolor=dpnl_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 5, dpnl_trades_text + " " + dpnl_limits, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 6: ADR Exhaustion
    adr_text = not enable_adr_filter ? "OFF" : str.tostring(adr_pct_used, "0") + "% of " + str.tostring(adr_val, "#.#") + "pt"
    adr_col = not enable_adr_filter ? color.new(color.gray, 80) : adr_pct_used >= adr_exhaust_pct ? color.new(#FF0000, 40) : adr_pct_used >= adr_tighten_pct ? color.new(color.orange, 50) : color.new(color.green, 60)
    adr_status = adr_pct_used >= adr_exhaust_pct ? "⛔ EXHAUSTED" : adr_tightening ? "⚡ TIGHTENED" : "✓ OK"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 6, "ADR", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 6, adr_text, bgcolor=adr_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 6, adr_status, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=adr_pct_used >= adr_exhaust_pct ? color.red : adr_tightening ? color.orange : color.green, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 7: Bollinger Bands
    bb_now_text = bb_squeeze_release ? "🔓 RELEASED" : bb_is_squeezed ? "⛔ SQUEEZE" : price_at_lower_bb ? "AT LOWER" : price_at_upper_bb ? "AT UPPER" : price_below_mid ? "LOWER HALF" : price_above_mid ? "UPPER HALF" : "MID"
    bb_dash_gate_l = bb_ok_long ? "✓" : "✗"
    bb_dash_gate_s = bb_ok_short ? "✓" : "✗"
    bb_conf_col = bb_squeeze_release ? color.new(#00FF00, 30) : bb_is_squeezed ? color.new(#FF0000, 40) : (bb_ok_long or bb_ok_short) ? color.new(color.green, 50) : color.new(color.gray, 70)
    bb_width_text = str.tostring(bb_width_pts, "#.#") + "/" + str.tostring(bb_squeeze_threshold, "#.#") + "pt"
    bb_tf_label = bb_tf == "D" ? "D" : bb_tf == "W" ? "W" : bb_tf == "M" ? "M" : bb_tf + "m"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 7, "BB (" + bb_tf_label + ")", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 7, bb_now_text, bgcolor=bb_conf_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 7, bb_is_squeezed ? bb_width_text : "L:" + bb_dash_gate_l + " S:" + bb_dash_gate_s, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=bb_is_squeezed ? color.red : color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 8: HMA Gate (v2.0.0/v2.0.3)
    hma_gate_text = hma_above_ema21 ? "HMA > 21 ▲" : "HMA < 21 ▼"
    hma_gate_col  = hma_above_ema21 ? color.new(color.green, 50) : color.new(color.red, 50)
    hma_slope_text = hma_rising ? "▲ RISING" : hma_falling ? "▼ FALLING" : "— FLAT"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 8, "HMA Gate", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 8, hma_gate_text, bgcolor=hma_gate_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 8, hma_slope_text, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=hma_rising ? color.green : hma_falling ? color.red : color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 9: EMA Stack (v2.0.0 — 21/34/50)
    trend_text = ema_stacked_bull ? "BULL 21>34>50" : ema_stacked_bear ? "BEAR 21<34<50" : "MIXED"
    trend_col  = ema_stacked_bull ? color.new(color.green, 50) : ema_stacked_bear ? color.new(color.red, 50) : color.new(color.gray, 70)
    ema_gap_21_34 = math.abs(ema_21 - ema_34)
    ema_gap_text = str.tostring(ema_gap_21_34, "#.#") + "pt gap"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 9, "EMA Stack", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 9, trend_text, bgcolor=trend_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 9, ema_gap_text, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=ema_gap_21_34 < 5 ? color.orange : color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 10: Cross-Wave Ratio (v2.0.0)
    xwave_ratio_l = prev_bull_wave > 0 ? prev_bear_wave / prev_bull_wave : na
    xwave_ratio_s = prev_bear_wave > 0 ? prev_bull_wave / prev_bear_wave : na
    xwave_display = ema_stacked_bull ? nz(xwave_ratio_l, 0.0) : ema_stacked_bear ? nz(xwave_ratio_s, 0.0) : 0.0
    xwave_pass    = xwave_long_ok or xwave_short_ok
    xwave_col     = xwave_pass ? color.new(color.green, 50) : ema_stacked_bull or ema_stacked_bear ? color.new(color.gray, 60) : color.new(color.gray, 80)
    xwave_text    = ema_stacked_bull or ema_stacked_bear ? str.tostring(xwave_display * 100, "0") + "% ≤" + str.tostring(xwave_threshold * 100, "0") + "%" : "—"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 10, "XWave Ratio", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 10, xwave_pass ? "✓ WEAK" : xwave_text != "—" ? "· CONTESTED" : "· NO STACK", bgcolor=xwave_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 10, xwave_text, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=xwave_pass ? color.green : color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 11: Spread Efficiency Qualifier (v2.1.1)
    seq_col    = seq_ok ? color.new(color.green, 50) : color.new(color.gray, 70)
    seq_vol_txt    = has_vol ? str.tostring(vol_safe, "#,##0") + " vs " + str.tostring(vol_sma_seq, "#,##0") : "no vol"
    seq_sprd_txt   = str.tostring(spread_current, "#.##") + " vs " + str.tostring(spread_sma_seq, "#.##")
    seq_status = seq_ok ? "✓ ABSORB" : vol_safe > vol_sma_seq ? "· SPRD HIGH" : spread_current < spread_sma_seq ? "· VOL LOW" : "· NO SIGNAL"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 11, "Sprd Effic", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 11, seq_status, bgcolor=seq_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 11, "V:" + seq_vol_txt, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=seq_ok ? color.green : color.gray, text_size=size.tiny)

    // Row 12: Effort vs Result (v2.1.0)
    er_pass     = er_long_ok or er_short_ok
    er_col      = er_pass ? color.new(color.green, 50) : bear_er_ratio > 0.0 or bull_er_ratio > 0.0 ? color.new(color.gray, 60) : color.new(color.gray, 80)
    er_src_lbl  = use_body_disp ? "Body" : "Wick"
    er_bear_txt = bear_er_ratio > 0.0 ? str.tostring(bear_er_ratio, "0.0") : "—"
    er_bull_txt = bull_er_ratio > 0.0 ? str.tostring(bull_er_ratio, "0.0") : "—"
    er_status   = er_long_ok ? "✓ BEAR EXHSTD" : er_short_ok ? "✓ BULL EXHSTD" : bear_er_ratio > 0.0 or bull_er_ratio > 0.0 ? "· LOW EFFORT" : "· NO DATA"
    er_detail   = "B:" + er_bear_txt + " U:" + er_bull_txt + " [" + er_src_lbl + "]"
    table.cell(dash, 0, 12, "E/R Ratio", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 12, er_status, bgcolor=er_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 12, er_detail, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=er_pass ? color.green : color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 13: Confluence Counter (9 factors — v2.1.1)
    conf_display = math.max(conf_total_long, conf_total_short)
    conf_detail_l = (conf_flip_long > 0 ? "F" : "·") + (conf_vol_long > 0 ? "V" : "·") + (conf_bb_long > 0 ? "B" : "·") + (conf_session > 0 ? "S" : "·") + (conf_hma_long > 0 ? "Hpx" : "···") + (conf_ema_long > 0 ? "E" : "·") + (conf_xwave_long > 0 ? "W" : "·") + (conf_er_long > 0 ? "R" : "·") + (conf_seq > 0 ? "Q" : "·")
    conf_detail_s = (conf_flip_short > 0 ? "F" : "·") + (conf_vol_short > 0 ? "V" : "·") + (conf_bb_short > 0 ? "B" : "·") + (conf_session > 0 ? "S" : "·") + (conf_hma_short > 0 ? "Hpx" : "···") + (conf_ema_short > 0 ? "E" : "·") + (conf_xwave_short > 0 ? "W" : "·") + (conf_er_short > 0 ? "R" : "·") + (conf_seq > 0 ? "Q" : "·")
    conf_col = conf_display >= 6 ? color.new(color.green, 40) : conf_display >= 4 ? color.new(color.yellow, 50) : color.new(color.gray, 70)
    conf_dir_text = conf_total_long > conf_total_short ? "L:" + conf_detail_l : conf_total_short > conf_total_long ? "S:" + conf_detail_s : "L:" + conf_detail_l
    table.cell(dash, 0, 13, "Confluence", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 13, str.tostring(conf_display) + "/" + str.tostring(conf_max), bgcolor=conf_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 13, conf_dir_text, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 14: Win Rate
    wr_col = win_rate >= 60 ? color.new(color.green, 50) : win_rate >= 50 ? color.new(color.yellow, 50) : color.new(color.red, 50)
    table.cell(dash, 0, 14, "Win Rate", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 14, str.tostring(win_rate, "0.0") + "%", bgcolor=wr_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 14, str.tostring(closed) + " closed", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 15: Net P&L
    pnl_col = net_pnl >= 0 ? color.new(color.green, 50) : color.new(color.red, 50)
    table.cell(dash, 0, 15, "Net P&L", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 15, "$" + str.tostring(net_pnl, "#,##0"), bgcolor=pnl_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 15, "DD:$" + str.tostring(max_dd, "#,##0"), bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.red, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 16: Profit Factor
    pf_col = pf >= 2.0 ? color.new(color.green, 50) : pf >= 1.5 ? color.new(color.yellow, 50) : color.new(color.red, 50)
    table.cell(dash, 0, 16, "Prof Factor", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 16, str.tostring(pf, "0.00") + "x", bgcolor=pf_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.normal)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 16, "W:" + str.tostring(wins) + " L:" + str.tostring(losses), bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 17: Expectancy
    exp_col = expectancy > 0 ? color.new(color.green, 60) : color.new(color.red, 60)
    table.cell(dash, 0, 17, "Expectancy", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 17, "$" + str.tostring(expectancy, "#,##0") + "/trade", bgcolor=exp_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 17, "per contract", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.tiny)

    // Row 18: Avg W/L
    table.cell(dash, 0, 18, "Avg W/L", bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 18, "$" + str.tostring(avg_win, "#,##0"), bgcolor=color.new(color.green, 65), text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 18, "$" + str.tostring(avg_loss, "#,##0"), bgcolor=color.new(color.red, 65), text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)

    // Row 19: Volume Method + Stats (v2.0.7: enhanced for Wave Compare)
    wave_exh_clx = (wave_use_exhaustion ? "E" : "·") + (wave_use_climax ? "C" : "·")
    wave_trigger = use_wave ? (wave_bear_exhausted or wave_bull_exhausted ? "EXH" : wave_bear_climax or wave_bull_climax ? "CLX" : "—") : ""
    wave_info = use_wave ? wave_trigger + " B:" + str.tostring(prev_bull_wave, "#,##0") + " S:" + str.tostring(prev_bear_wave, "#,##0") : ""
    roc_info  = use_roc ? "ROC:" + str.tostring(vol_roc_val, "0.0") + "%" : ""
    z_info    = use_z ? "Z:" + str.tostring(vol_z, "0.1") : ""
    method_info = use_wave ? wave_info : use_roc ? roc_info : use_z ? z_info : "—"
    vol_pass = vol_bottom_raw or vol_peak_raw
    vol_col  = vol_pass ? color.new(color.green, 50) : color.new(color.gray, 70)
    vol_method_detail = use_wave ? vol_method_label + " [" + wave_exh_clx + "]" : vol_method_label
    table.cell(dash, 0, 19, "Vol " + vol_method_detail, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 1, 19, vol_pass ? "✓ EXHAUSTION" : "· scanning", bgcolor=vol_col, text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    table.cell(dash, 2, 19, method_info, bgcolor=bg_row, text_color=color.gray, text_size=size.tiny)

    // Row 20: Debug Gate Diagnostic
    if debug_mode
        table.cell(dash, 0, 20, "🔧 DEBUG", bgcolor=color.new(#FF6B00, 30), text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
        table.cell(dash, 1, 20, "ALL GATES BYPASSED", bgcolor=color.new(#FF6B00, 30), text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
        table.cell(dash, 2, 20, "flip only", bgcolor=color.new(#FF6B00, 50), text_color=txt, text_size=size.small)
    else
        flip_ok = flip_to_bull or flip_to_bear
        raw_flip = raw_flip_bull or raw_flip_bear
        dbg_flip = flip_ok ? "✓" : raw_flip ? "✗" + str.tostring(prev_wave_len) + "b<" + str.tostring(min_wave_len) : "·"
        dbg_vol  = not req_V or not debug_require_vol ? "OFF" : (vol_pass ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_bb   = bb_is_squeezed ? "SQZ" : (bb_ok_long or bb_ok_short) ? "✓" : "✗"  // confluence status only
        dbg_trend = not debug_require_trend ? "OFF" : ((trend_gate_long or trend_gate_short) ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_hpx  = not req_H ? "OFF" : ((hpx_gate_long and flip_to_bull) or (hpx_gate_short and flip_to_bear) ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_ema  = not req_E ? "OFF" : (ema_stacked_bull or ema_stacked_bear ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_xwv  = not req_W ? "OFF" : (xwave_long_ok or xwave_short_ok ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_er   = not req_R ? "OFF" : (er_long_ok or er_short_ok ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_seq  = not req_Q ? "OFF" : (seq_ok ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_sess = not req_S or not debug_require_session ? "OFF" : (in_session ? "✓" : "✗")
        dbg_adr  = not enable_adr_filter ? "OFF" : (adr_ok ? "✓" : "✗" + str.tostring(adr_pct_used, "0") + "%")
        dbg_chop = not debug_require_chop ? "OFF" : (not is_choppy ? "✓" : "✗" + str.tostring(avg_wave_len, "0.1") + "b")
        table.cell(dash, 0, 20, "🔧 GATES", bgcolor=color.new(#1a1a2e, 0), text_color=color.orange, text_size=size.small)
        table.cell(dash, 1, 20, "F:" + dbg_flip + " V:" + dbg_vol + " BB(c):" + dbg_bb + " TR:" + dbg_trend, bgcolor=color.new(#16213e, 0), text_color=color.orange, text_size=size.small)
        table.cell(dash, 2, 20, "Hpx:" + dbg_hpx + " E:" + dbg_ema + " W:" + dbg_xwv + " R:" + dbg_er + " Q:" + dbg_seq + " SS:" + dbg_sess + " CH:" + dbg_chop + " ADR:" + dbg_adr, bgcolor=color.new(#16213e, 0), text_color=color.orange, text_size=size.small)

// ============================================================================
// ALERT CONDITIONS
// ============================================================================
alertcondition(vol_bottom, title="🟢 VOL BOTTOM (Long)", message="VEB — Volume Exhaustion Bottom. Long entry signal fired.")
alertcondition(vol_peak,   title="🔴 VOL PEAK (Short)",  message="VEP — Volume Exhaustion Peak. Short entry signal fired.")
alertcondition(vol_bottom and is_short, title="🔄 FLATTEN→LONG", message="Flattening shorts, entering long on VOL BOTTOM.")
alertcondition(vol_peak and is_long,    title="🔄 FLATTEN→SHORT", message="Flattening longs, entering short on VOL PEAK.")
alertcondition(bb_squeeze_release, title="🔓 BB SQUEEZE RELEASED", message="Bollinger Bands expanding out of squeeze — watch for first signal.")
alertcondition(is_choppy and not is_choppy[1], title="⛔ CHOP DETECTED", message="Wave length chop detector activated — signals blocked.")
alertcondition(not is_choppy and is_choppy[1], title="✅ CHOP CLEARED", message="Wave length chop detector cleared — signals re-enabled.")

// ============================================================================
// SIGNAL ROUTER — Hidden meta-signals for webhook bundling (v2.0.9)
// ============================================================================
// These aggregate ALL long entries into one alert and ALL short entries into
// one alert. Use for ATS/QuantLynk routing where you don't need to distinguish
// between confluence grades — just "go long" or "go short".
//
// Alert setup:
//   1. Create alert on this strategy
//   2. Condition: "Any alert() function call"
//   3. Message: Leave default (alert provides the payload)
//   4. Webhook URL: Your ATS/QuantLynk endpoint
//
// The router uses alert() with dynamic JSON payloads including confluence
// count, wave length, and entry price.
// ============================================================================

grp_router = "📡 Signal Router"
router_enabled = input.bool(false, "Enable Signal Router Alerts", group=grp_router,
     tooltip="When ON, fires alert() calls for ANY long or ANY short signal with JSON payloads.\nUse with 'Any alert() function call' condition.\nKeeps existing VEB/VEP labels and strategy entries unchanged.\n(Default: OFF)")
router_webhook_url = input.string("", "Router Webhook URL (optional)", group=grp_router,
     tooltip="If provided, included in alert payload for multi-endpoint routing.\n(Default: empty)")

// Router signals — fire on ANY qualifying entry (same as vol_bottom/vol_peak)
router_long  = vol_bottom and daily_ok
router_short = vol_peak and daily_ok

// Build JSON payloads
router_payload_long = '{' +
     '"action":"buy",' +
     '"symbol":"' + syminfo.ticker + '",' +
     '"price":' + str.tostring(close) + ',' +
     '"confluence":' + str.tostring(conf_total_long) + ',' +
     '"conf_max":' + str.tostring(conf_max) + ',' +
     '"wave_len":' + str.tostring(prev_wave_len) + ',' +
     '"tp":' + str.tostring(close + tp_pts) + ',' +
     '"sl":' + str.tostring(close - sl_pts) + ',' +
     '"trigger":"VES_ROUTER_LONG"' +
     '}'

router_payload_short = '{' +
     '"action":"sell",' +
     '"symbol":"' + syminfo.ticker + '",' +
     '"price":' + str.tostring(close) + ',' +
     '"confluence":' + str.tostring(conf_total_short) + ',' +
     '"conf_max":' + str.tostring(conf_max) + ',' +
     '"wave_len":' + str.tostring(prev_wave_len) + ',' +
     '"tp":' + str.tostring(close - tp_pts) + ',' +
     '"sl":' + str.tostring(close + sl_pts) + ',' +
     '"trigger":"VES_ROUTER_SHORT"' +
     '}'

// Fire router alerts (hidden from chart — no labels, just alert())
if router_enabled and router_long
    alert(router_payload_long, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)

if router_enabled and router_short
    alert(router_payload_short, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)